title: fruit salad
directions: Fold pudding into Cool Whip.
Drain all canned fruit.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken
directions: Place chicken in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour Italian dressing over all.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can onions around and under chicken. Combine water, bouillon and Italian seasoning together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 3 minutes more.

title: baklava
directions: Melt butter over low heat (do not brown) and skim off foam as it rises.
Remove from heat and let set for 2 or 3 minutes.
Use the clear yellow butter and discard the solids.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir oil into butter and brush the sides and bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan.
Fold a sheet of filo in half crosswise and place in the buttered pan.
Press in and brush entire surface lightly with the oil and butter mixture.
Add another layer of filo, then butter, nuts and repeat until all filo and nuts are used.
A final layer of filo should be double (two folded sheets).

Brush all the remaining oil and butter over top. With a small, sharp knife, score the top of the pastry with parallel diagonal lines about 1/2-inch deep and 2 inches apart, then cross them diagonally to form diamond shapes.
Bake in the middle of the oven at 350° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for about 45 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes.
Rub with oil.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool to handle.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove cooked potatoes to large mixing bowl.
Mash with cream cheese, milk, onion salt, butter and pepper.
Push through potato ricer.
Pile back into skins.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix milk, sugar and cocoa; bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add oats first to the boiling mixture to cook them, then add butter next to melt it. Then add peanut butter and vanilla; mix real good. Drop by spoon on wax paper or foil.

title: crock-pot butter beans
directions: Wash beans. Soak, covered, in water overnight. Drain and place in crock-pot with other ingredients. Cover and cook on high setting 5 to 6 hours until tender.

title: cheesy macaroni
directions: In a large saucepan, cook macaroni until tender.
Add broccoli and boil for about 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Return macaroni and broccoli to saucepan and add cheese, salt, egg and bacon bits. Mix well and pour into a baking dish.
Pour milk over mixture and bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak dry beans overnight by covering with 2-inches of water and 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain beans.
Fill to 2-inches above beans with fresh water and bring to a rapid boil.
Drain again and put in crock-pot.
Cover with 1-inch of water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour on high.
Cook 12 to 14 hours on low.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, bring to boil all ingredients except brandy and pastry.
Stir often and reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in brandy. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: corn meal sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and pinch of salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, corn meal and soda together 3 times.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add salt to the egg whites and beat until peaks form.
Fold in the beaten egg whites. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: hazel davis's refrigerator slaw
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except cabbage; pour over cabbage.
Leave in refrigerator as long as 3 weeks.

title: mock swiss steak
directions: Mix well and pat down on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares and brown in skillet in light oil.
Place meat in baking dish and cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 package Lipton dry onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 6 to 8-inch square pan.
Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes, until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes, according to thickness, until done. Test with toothpick.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder with milk.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts that have been lightly sprinkled with flour.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for about 60 minutes.
A toothpick will come out clean when it is done.

title: johnny cake
directions: Cream
shortening;
add
sugar and cream well.	Add egg yolks. Sift dry ingredients;
add to egg mix alternately with sour milk. Fold
in
beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan; bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container. Mix 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.
Warm, tasty drink for Christmas parties.

title: lollipops
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Continue boiling, without stirring, until a small amount is very brittle when dropped into cold water.
Cook slowly at end of cooking time so that the corn syrup will not discolor.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Stir only to mix.
Drop syrup quickly from tip of spoon onto a flat, buttered surface.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream first three ingredients until real fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time creaming after each. Gradually add flour, one cup at a time. Beat a long time then add milk and vanilla.
The trick to a good pound cake is taking the time to beat it really well. Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix together brown sugar, syrup and margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Add baking soda and vanilla (be careful, it will start to bubble up).
Remove pan from stove and pour over popcorn.
Mix the popcorn with the caramel sauce.
Enjoy!

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: You will need 2 1/2-inch foil baking cups.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Line bottom of large shallow bowl with lettuce; top with cauliflower florets and onion slices.
Using a rubber scraper, spread mayonnaise over entire surface of salad.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits (do not toss).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, toss salad to combine.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute hamburger or sausage, onion and pepperoni.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in baking dish.
Toss cooked spaghetti in melted margarine.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Layer half of Swiss cheese, meat mixture and Mozzarella.
Turn layer all of the mushrooms.
Sprinkle oregano and basil on top.
Layer remaining Swiss cheese, meat mixture and Mozzarella.
Top with 1 can tomato sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chilies in layers in bottom of pan.
Cover with cheese.
Blend eggs, salt, milk and Bisquick.
Mix and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter and cream cheese.
In separate bowl, mix together sugar and Cool Whip.
Add all ingredients together and beat with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 crusts.
Keep refrigerated.
Top with chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: skillet barbecue pork chops
directions: In large skillet with a tight lid, brown chops in oil over medium heat about 5 minutes on each side.
Pour off excess fat. Sprinkle celery, brown sugar, lemon juice and seasonings evenly over chops.
Pour tomato sauce over chops last.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook meat and drain. Put meat in crock-pot to keep it warm. Add small cubes of cheese, soup and picante sauce. Serve warm with your choice of dipping chips.

title: quick baked beans(yields 9 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in greased casserole dish. Top with bacon slices.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer until brown and bubbly.

title: gingerbread man
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit salt and soda, or if using Wondra flour, add 3 tablespoons milk.

title: ground turkey and noodles
directions: Brown turkey; add onion, salt, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire.
Add noodles and tomatoes.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° until browned.
Top with cheese, if desired. Serves 8.

title: red bean and hominy salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Sprinkle with bacon bits. Cover with Ranch dressing.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Dice all peppers.
Combine with water.
Put in blender and mix.
Add peppers to vinegar and sugar and bring to rapid boil for 4 minutes only, using a very large pot since this tends to be very hot and may boil over.
Remove from heat and add Certo and food coloring.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: krumkaker
directions: Mix together the slightly beaten eggs, sugar and melted butter.
Add flour and cream.
Mix with beater until smooth.
Bake on hot krumkake iron.
Add a little more flour if the cakes are lacy.

title: beef paprika
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
Make gravy thickened with remaining 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.

title: turkey rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine soup, milk, thyme, lemon juice and pepper in a large mixing bowl; set aside 1/2 cup of mixture. Add turkey and rice to mixture in bowl and toss well to mix. Lightly coat an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray.
Spoon turkey mixture into the dish.
Arrange the broccoli on top.
Pour the reserved 1/2 cup of soup mixture evenly over all.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, oranges, orange rind and nuts together. Add sugar. Mix and let set. Extra apples and oranges can be added according to size.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Spread pretzels in bottom of dish.
Pour butter over pretzels. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of sugar over butter.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over first mixture.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; add strawberries.
Stir until thickened.
Pour over 2nd layer.
Cool.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans. Pour into the pastry shell.
Top with pecans and bake for 40 minutes or until set.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups white sugar.
Add eggs and cream again.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together salt, baking powder and flour.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts together.
Grease and flour the bottoms of two (9-inch) cake pans.
Spoon half the batter into the pans. Sprinkle with half the nut mixture.
Top with remaining batter and nut mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 coffee cakes; 12 servings.

title: strawberries in a blender
directions: In blender, combine strawberries, sugar, egg, spices and milk; blend until mixture is a thick "shake" consistency.
Good for breakfast, snack or dessert.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water and set aside.
Cream together 1/2 cup margarine, 1 cup white sugar, 1 cup brown sugar and 2 eggs.
Mix flour, salt, nutmeg, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Add to butter mixture, then add oatmeal.
Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven.
Add mixture of margarine, 1 cup brown sugar, 1 egg, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread evenly over cake and return to oven and brown.

title: bechamel sauce(yields 1 cup)
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add the flour and blend well for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Slowly stir in the warmed milk and add the onion and bay leaf.
Cook and stir with a wooden spoon until sauce thickens and coats the back of spoon. Place in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes. Take out and strain; add salt and nutmeg.

title: no bake cookies #1
directions: Mix together on top of the stove the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Let boil 1 minute.
Remove.
Stir while mixing in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop on wax paper.
If too thin, add more oats.
If too thick, add little more milk.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mash butter mixed with sugar, then brown sugar and vanilla, then the egg. Mix all together with flour and chocolate chips. Bake at 300° until golden brown. If desired, more chocolate chips can be added.

title: beer batter oysters
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Mix in pepper.
Beat the egg and oil together and mix in hot sauce, beer and lemon juice. Gradually add this to the flour.
Stir well to avoid a lumpy batter.
Pat oysters dry on paper towel and put 5 or 6 at a time in the batter.
Coat oysters evenly.
Take oysters from batter and place in hot oil at 375° for about 1 minute or until brown.
Remove from oil and place on paper towel.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Mix salad dressing and soy sauce for use as marinade.
Set aside 1/4 cup of marinade.
Add chicken to remainder of marinade. Cover and chill at least 1 hour, may do longer, such as overnight. Saute onion in reserved 1/4 cup marinade over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes; set aside.
Drain chicken.
Grill over hot coals about 5 minutes on each side or until done.
Baste twice with marinade. Cut chicken into 1/4-inch strips.
Wrap tortillas and heat according to package directions.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar slowly.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in cornflakes, nuts and coconut.
Drop on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: german gooseberry pie
directions: Place gooseberries into an unbaked pie crust. Beat sugar, eggs, salt and milnot together and pour over berries. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: fabulous low-fat, high carb soup(servings:  4)
directions: Brown turkey with onions and garlic.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together and beat well until light and fluffy the sugar and shortening. Add and beat well eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Press onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned and crisp.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Melt the butter over low heat and mix in the peanut butter. Then use a big spoon to drizzle it over the popcorn.

title: stroganoff meat balls
directions: Combine ground round, milk, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper. Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
brown in 1/4 stick oleo.
Remove from pan.
In 1/4 stick oleo, cook onions and mushrooms with paprika until tender.
Sprinkle flour over mixture.
Stir in beef bouillon.
Return meat balls to sauce. Cover, simmer 10 minutes. Stir in Worcestershire and sour cream.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: grandmother mcdaniel's pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: spring peas and carrots
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine first 3 ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High 5 minutes until tender-crisp.
Add margarine and stir to combine.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes. Let stand 1 minute.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix undiluted chicken soup and cooked rice.
Fold in onion, celery, water chestnuts and chicken.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Place crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Chop broccoli.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Chop red onion.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onion.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimparoni salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: carrot balls
directions: Combine cheese, carrots, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in eggs and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant, salt well and peel.
Let stand in salt with enough water to cover for 15 minutes.
Rinse.
Salt again; let stand for 10 minutes.
Rinse, cook until done.
Beat egg; add mushroom soup and beat.
Add eggplant (about 1 cup); add onion and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into baking dish, cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Cover with crushed crackers, then cover with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sue's zucchini bread with glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.
So easy and as good as pecan.

title: summer squash tart
directions: Combine squash, water and salt in saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook until just tender. Drain well.
Divide squash in half. Combine 1/2 with melted butter in bowl. Coarsely mash mixture. Stir in eggs, sour cream and onion.
Gently stir in remaining half of sliced squash.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spread in baked shell and bake at 350° until knife comes out clean when inserted in center. Serve hot or cold.
Most people prefer hot.

title: stuffed vegetables
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water in a large skillet for 10 minutes.
Drain, scoop out insides, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Mash inside; drain well.
Put shell in a shallow baking dish.
Remove casings from sausage; break up meal.
Cook sausage in same skillet 5 minutes.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender, 3 minutes. Stir in mashed zucchini and bread crumbs.
Spoon mixture into shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until piping hot.
Serves 6. Great as a side dish or for hors d'oeuvres.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dessert salad
directions: Chill cherry pie filling, drained crushed pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and pecans. Mix in Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight. (Keep refrigerated for best results.)

title: bread stuffing for turkey
directions: In a large skillet in 2 tablespoons of liquid Butter Buds, cook and stir onion and celery until onion is tender.
Stir in about 1/3 of the bread cubes.
Turn into a deep bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Bake in the turkey or a casserole dish that has been covered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ruth's famous chowder
directions: Dice potatoes and boil (save water).
Saute diced onions and celery and parsley in 1/2 stick of margarine.
Put everything in the pot (except the fish) and bring to a boil.
Cut the fish into medium-sized pieces (size not important as they cook apart).
Add fish to boiling pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan biscuit ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk and stir lightly to blend.
Knead gently about 10 times.
Form into 16 balls.
Combine butter and cheese and roll each ball in mixture. Place in single layer in a well-greased 5-cup ring mold.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before unmolding.
Serves 8.

title: big raisin cake(frugal fruit cake)
directions: Boil raisins in 2 c. water for 15 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add next 3 ingredients to cooled raisins.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix together well.
Grease 3 loaf pans, then dust with flour.
Bake slowly at 325 degrees for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cakes from pan and cool right side up on rack. This cake will keep for several weeks and does not crumble when shipped.

title: white chili
directions: Place beans in a heavy large pot.
Add enough water to cover by at least 3-inches and soak overnight.
Place chicken in a large pan, add cold water to cover and bring to a simmer.
Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin; cut into cubes.
Drain beans.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine in a large mixer bowl all ingredients; mix at low speed until a dough forms.
Shape into balls using a rounded teaspoonful of dough. Roll balls in additional sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Top each hot cookie immediately with a candy kiss, pressing down so cookie cracks around edge.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: peach chiffon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into pan.
Mix Knox gelatine with cold water, then hot water.
Set aside.
Mix peaches and sugar.
Mix with gelatine.
Pour in pie pan.
Top with Cool Whip and corn flake crumbs.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients; mix until smooth; add nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, peanut butter, oleomargarine and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from fire.
Add nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
(Do not bake.)
Cool; ready to serve.

title: snickers cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Pour half into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add onions and cheese, stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: dark orange cake
directions: Butter and flour a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
In large bowl of mixer, cream sugar, butter and eggs; add vanilla.
Stir or sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture, stirring well after each addition.
In a food processor or grinder, finely grind the raisins, nuts and orange (peel and all). Reserve 2 tablespoons of this mixture for Orange Frosting.
Add the remaining ground orange mix to cake batter.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center is clean.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: creamy cucumber soup
directions: Combine soup, milk, cucumber, green pepper, olives and hot sauce in blender or processor. Blend 2 minutes. Add sour cream and lemon juice; mix well. Chill at least 4 hours. Garnish with sliced cucumber and paprika. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon in large bowl.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces (quarters) and coat with sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Drop coated biscuits into Bundt pan.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Pour over the top of biscuits in the Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn over onto plate and let everyone just pull the pieces off like monkeys!

title: jello shots
directions: Dissolve gelatin with boiling water.
Add vodka and Schnapps. Pour into candy cups.
Refrigerate until set.

title: apple crisp again
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place dry ingredients in a bowl and mix to blend. Add soft butter and blend well
with pastry blender or fork.
Arrange apples in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread oatmeal mixture on top of apples and press down lightly. Bake for 30 minutes or until topping is brown and apples are tender when tested with a fork. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cherry divinity cake
directions: Mix first eight ingredients and bake at 350° until done; makes 5 layers.
Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt until it will spin a good thread.
Pour half of mixture over stiffly beaten egg whites to which baking powder has been added.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Add remaining syrup mixture and again.
Add chopped nuts, vanilla and cherries.
Mix and spread on cake layers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together; let set for at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: oven pancake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mixture of eggs, milk and flour. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or at 350° for 20 minutes. Knife should come out clean.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: company chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture; marinate, covered, in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight. Dip chicken pieces in crumbs to coat.
Place on shallow baking pan (not touching).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine butter and oil; pour over.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ice cream grasshopper
directions: In a blender container, combine vanilla ice cream, the white creme de cacao and the green creme de menthe.
Cover and blend just until smooth.
Pour into a chilled champagne glass or wine glass.
Garnish with a mint sprig, if desired.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Place frozen vegetables in 1 1/2-quart non-metal baking dish. Cook at High power in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in half the cheese and the remaining ingredients.
Cook 6 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle with remaining cheese and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean chicken pieces and place them in a glass baking pan, single layer.

title: pumpkin cake with cream cheese frosting(very good)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, measure all ingredients except walnuts. With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed.
Increase speed to high and beat 5 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into 1-inch greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool cake completely on rack. Frost cake with Cream Cheese Frosting. Refrigerate.
Makes 16 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into 1-inch strips.
Dice onion.
Stir all ingredients together in roaster with cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh green beans and potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into small bite size pieces.
Place in water to cover and boil until tender.
Wash and snap the green beans.
Place in large pan of boiling water and other ingredients, except potatoes.
Cook until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Once beans are tender, reduce to simmer.
Add potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Wash and quarter all fruit, coring apples and removing seeds and hard ends of oranges and lemons.
Do not peel any of fruit.
Grind all in food processor or grinder to desired size.
Blend in sugar and allow to marinate one day before using.
Keep in refrigerator.
This mixture and chopped pecans can be added to strawberry gelatin for a molded salad.

title: chicken and cheese crescent chimichangas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add chicken; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and then let cool.
Then add sugar and beat.
Then beat in eggs first and then flour.
Fold in nuts. Bake at 350°.
While cake is hot cover with marshmallows, then frost with butter cocoa frosting.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, combine brown sugar and margarine.

Cook and stir over low heat until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat; arrange pineapple slices and cherries in skillet in sugar mixture. In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Pour batter over fruit in skillet.
Bake in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Invert warm cake on serving platter.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Chop vegetables in blender.
Drain off water.
Add to sour cream, Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Separate 1 egg and beat the yolk well. Gradually add water to yolk. Set aside. Mix other ingredients in a doubler boiler and when boiling, add 3 tablespoons to the egg yolk-water combination. Stir. Add yolk-water mixture to pan and mix together. Pour over vanilla ice cream while hot.

title: beef strips oriental
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain.
Add 1 cup water, soy sauce and garlic to drippings.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add carrot, celery and mushrooms.
Cover and continue cooking 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine the cornstarch and cold water and blend well. Gradually add cornstarch mixture to hot meat and vegetables. Stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: spaghetti louisiana style
directions: Melt shortening, flour and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add cayenne pepper, mustard, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Remove from heat.
Add cleaned shrimp to hot sauce.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain spaghetti.
Place on platter.
Cover with hot shrimp sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: thelma's best beef liver and smothered onions
directions: Combine all the seasonings in a small bowl.
Mix with about 1 cup of the flour; set aside.
Fry bacon in a large heavy skillet until crisp. Drain. Add enough oil to bacon drippings to make 1/4-inch oil in bottom of skillet.
Dredge liver in seasoned flour.
Fry in hot oil until browned (approximately 2 minutes on each side).
In a separate skillet, heat bacon drippings from liver.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until browned.
Serve over liver.

title: donna's waffle iron cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Drop in cookie size globs onto hot, oiled waffle iron.
Close cover and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and frost while warm.

title: milk chocolate delight cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs until fluffy.
Add milk with vinegar and beat.
Beat in flour.
Add cocoa and soda to boiling water and blend in slowly.
Pour into two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: keith's kentucky pulled pork
directions: Mix all the spices together and hand rub the shoulder on both sides!
Make sure you use all the mix.
Pour the rest on top if left over.

title: yucky chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Combine the mayonnaise and mustard. Add to chicken mixture. Chill several hours or overnight (best).
Add noodles just before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Bring to a boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Cool and pour over vegetables. Let stand 24 hours.
Will keep for 1 week in refrigerator.

title: glady's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add together soda in sour cream.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Let stand 2 hours in refrigerator and then roll out.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake about 8 minutes at 375°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the lettuce, peas, celery, onions and peppers.
Add layer of salad dressing and sugar.
Sprinkle bacon bits and grated cheese on top.
Chill overnight or 4 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pineapple and mix together carrots, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then add to liquid mixture and beat again.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 2 ingredients.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Pour into a jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Chill until firm.
Use cookie cutters to cut shapes.
Use extra pieces with Cool Whip in a bowl.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup cream to make paste.
Stir paste until smooth, then add the remaining cup of cream.
Beat lightly.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Filling must boil all over in little heat bubbles.

title: no fuss supper
directions: Sprinkle meat with garlic salt, pepper and salt.
In covered baking dish, combine soups and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with boiled potatoes, rice or noodles.
This makes a delicious gravy and it's fast.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Crumble into a dish.
Pour pudding (prepare as directed on box) on top of cake.
Slice strawberries; dump on top of pudding (save a few for on top).
Spread whipped cream on top.
Arrange a few strawberries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 10 minutes, then lower to 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Mix water, vinegar and sugar and bring to boil until well dissolved.
Stir often.
Let stand until well cooled.
Drain off juice from the quart of dill pickles.
Cut pickles into medium size strips.
Replace pickles in same jar.
Pour in sugar mixture and replace lid.
In 2 or 3 days they will be delicious sweet pickles.

title: seasoned salt cajun blend(salt free)
directions: Buy bargain bread or use some that is several days old.
Toast it in the oven.
Place in a plastic bag and roll into crumbs with rolling pin.
Then add garlic powder, dried oregano, parsley and dried, minced onion.

title: jellied cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries, drain and remove stems.
Chop rather fairly fine.
Add sugar.
Let cranberry mixture stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle gelatin over apple juice in a small saucepan.
Soften for 5 minutes.
Place over low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add gelatin mixture, celery, apple and nuts to cranberries; mix well.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm, about 6 to 8 hours or overnight. To unmold, run a small spatula around the edge of mold.
Invert on a serving plate.
Place a hot, damp dishcloth on bottom of mold; shake to release.
Repeat procedure, if necessary.
Makes 8 servings.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain and cool. Add all ingredients together. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat and bring to boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over oats.
Mix well.
Spoon on waxed paper.
Let set.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: plain molasses candy
directions: Put butter in a pan and melt. Add molasses and sugar. Stir until dissolved. Boil steadily until a
drop can be placed into cold water and will harden. Stir constantly.
Before removing from heat, put in vinegar. When cool enough to handle, pull with well buttered hands until candy is porous and light colored. Handle lightly.
Do not squeeze between hands. Cut with sharp knife and arrange on buttered plates to cool.

title: old fashioned lemon pound cake
directions: This is a scrumptious summer dessert and it's real pretty when cut.

title: sunshine cobbler
directions: Cook pie mix according to box directions using the 2 egg yolks.
Pour pie mix into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon fruit cocktail and nutmeg on top.
Make cake batter per box using egg whites and extract.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: cheese cake
directions: *I use the juice of whole lemon, or you can use ReaLemon juice in bottle.

title: butterball coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan. Melt in small saucepan the butter.
Mix in bowl the sugar and cinnamon.
Remove and separate biscuits.
Dip each biscuit into butter, then roll in the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place 15 of the biscuits around the outer part of the pan, overlapping to make a circle.
Overlap the remaining 5 biscuits to fill the center of the pan.
Pour any leftover melted butter over the biscuits.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add bouillon cubes and boil 3 minutes. Add broccoli and boil 5 minutes.
Add Velveeta.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a bowl, mix together the peanut butter, condensed milk and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Roll candy into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in chopped nuts.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put ground chuck, bell peppers, onions, mushrooms, salt, pepper, oregano, basil leaves, parsley flakes and garlic powder in saucepan and cook over high heat until meat is done; stirring constantly.
(Salt, pepper, oregano, basil, garlic powder and parsley is to your liking.)
After meat mixture is done, turn heat down to low and add tomato sauce and ketchup.
Stir well and take off heat.

title: tortilla pizza
directions: Place tortillas on a flat surface.
Use 2 - 3 tablespoons of pizza sauce on each.
Spread sauce over whole tortilla.
Generously sprinkle cheeses over tortilla.
Add chopped ham and/or desired toppings.
Place each tortilla on a microwavable plate.
Microwave 2 - 5 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.
Cut into 6 - 8 pieces and serve as meal, snack, or appetizer.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into tiny balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Do not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes. Cut aluminum foil to fit cookie sheets.

title: joe's world famous stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cut top of pumpkin wide enough for hand to fit in and retain top as a lid.
Scoop out all seeds and string.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Set aside.
Cook diced onion in a small amount of oil until transparent (not brown).

title: tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Add tuna and corn.
Heat well.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and add 1/3 cup milk with 3/4 cup butter.
Put 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with the rest of milk and spread on cake.
Spread nuts on top of caramels along with chips.
Pour rest of batter on top and bake for another 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Add Marshmallow Creme and juices.
Blend together until smooth. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine egg, Crisco, milk, vanilla and brown sugar.
Mix until creamy.
Add flour, salt and soda until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yields 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: plum cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350° and grease pan. (I use a Bundt mold pan) and dust with flour.
Halve the plums, removing pits.
Place in a large bowl and sprinkle with the cinnamon and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Beat the eggs and gradually add the remaining sugar, oil, orange juice and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with the egg mixture. Pour half of the batter into the pan.
Layer with 1/3 of the plums, repeating for 2 more layers, ending with plums on top. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until golden on top and a toothpick comes out clean.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, run a knife around the cake to loosen.
Unmold on a plate and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serves 12 people.

title: lima cheese baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook until tender, 1/2 hour.
Put all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut and pour on cake while hot.
Take spoon and make dents in cake.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on cake and cover with frozen coconut.

title: no-cook egg white frosting
directions: Beat
egg
whites
with
electric
mixer
until fluffy. Gradually
pour white syrup into egg whites.
Continue beating until very	stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla and mix 1/2 minute. Spread on
9 x 12-inch chocolate cake.
Refrigerate cake after frosting.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add water and cooking oil to the cake mix and jello, then add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix.
Add strawberries.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° not quite 10 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix water and gelatin; set aside.
Heat cream cheese, mayo and tomato soup until smooth.
Add gelatin mixture to cream cheese, mayo and soup.
Remove from heat.
Add celery and onion.
Pour into greased mold and set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Before taking out, run under hot water.

title: congo punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze in two 5-quart pails.
Take out of freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale or similar pop just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: fresh homemade strawberry pie
directions: Brown pie crust in oven approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Wash, cap and cut up strawberries.
Mix in large bowl with jar of glaze. Pour into pie shell; top with Cool Whip.
This is an extra good and easy recipe that can be done in approximately 15 minutes. Good eating.

title: aunt lydia's chocolate cake
directions: Beat brown sugar, lard and eggs, then add sour or buttermilk. Add hot water, flour, salt, soda, vanilla and cocoa.
Very moist, good cake.

title: rice krispie-peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey in a Pyrex dish.
Microwave 20 seconds.
Stir.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mash in a pan.
Slice bananas over crust.
Make pudding.
Pour over top.
Top with lite Cool Whip.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-cook frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and beat on low for 1 minute, then on high 10 to 12 minutes.
The secret is in the beating, so do not underbeat.
Yields enough for an angel food or 2-layer cake.
Be sure cake is completely cooled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Put in 2 greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean. Also, good as muffins.

title: peanut butter oaties
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine the rolled oats, flour and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture thoroughly.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or just until edges are golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove onto cooling rack.

title: chicken tidbits parmesan(a heart healthy recipe)
directions: In large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon margarine over medium-high heat.
Add bread crumbs.
Stir until lightly browned.
Transfer to medium bowl; combine with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
In same skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons margarine over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, mustard and chicken.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon; toss with bread crumb mixture.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Trim off bottom of watermelon to make flat.
Cut out top. Scoop out pulp and mash.
Measure 1 gallon watermelon juice and set aside.	Combine sugar and water and bring to boil.
Add gallon watermelon juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Stir gently.
Serve in watermelon shell.
Serves 30.

title: easy dessert
directions: Use deep bowl and line bottom
with cookies.
Add half of pie filling, then half of Cool Whip.
Add other half of cherry pie filling and top with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Makes a light and beautiful dessert.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in heavy casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, wine and soup; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meatballs in cocktail sauce
directions: Up to Days Before Serving:
Shape meat in 1-inch balls.
Place on a jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pecan icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; add sugar, beating well. Add
eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and in a medium
mixing
bowl,
add	to creamed mixture, stirring well. Add vanilla and pecans, stirring well.

title: crab cakes
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and slowly saute green onions, celery, bell pepper,
garlic
and
parsley	until tender.
Add crabmeat and cook 3 to
5 minutes more.
Stir in half of bread crumbs and season with
salt
and
pepper
to taste.
Add eggs slowly to crab mixture
and
stir.	You
are
mixing
to get a consistency that you will
be
able
to
form crab cakes.
Add more bread crumbs if needed,
but
not
so as to lose the crab taste.
Remove
from
fire, then refrigerate until cool.
Make your
crab cakes, then dust in flour.
Dip in beaten egg, then pat in
bread	crumbs.
Let cakes set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Fry cakes in oil until golden brown.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill one hour before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent dough into 9 x 13-inch pan to form a crust. Brown and crumble the sausage.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over the dough.
Spread hash browns around evenly as you desire, over the sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over all as desired.
Finally, beat eggs and add 1/4 cup milk.
Pour egg mixture over everything.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until egg sets.
Cool slightly before eating.

title: perfection salad
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Add other ingredients.

title: barbecue
directions: Mince and brown in a small amount of Crisco in a heavy skillet the onions and celery.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Add carrots and crushed pineapple, including juice.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: irish cream
directions: In blender, stir eggs and remaining ingredients and stir well. Do not whip.
Bottle and refrigerate.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix together crab, butter, cheese, garlic powder and mayonnaise.
Spread muffins with mixture.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes until bubbly.
Cut in quarters to serve.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: baking powder rolls
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in butter and mix as for pie crust.
Beat eggs; add to milk and add to first mixture. Knead dough until it sticks together and is smooth.
Divide into 3 portions.
Roll each to thickness desired; spread on filling. Roll up as for jelly roll.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until brown.
While still warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: hawaiian chicken breasts
directions: Combine pineapple juice, ketchup, brown sugar, butter, vinegar, cornstarch, salt, chili powder, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce in small saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.

title: pizza crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cut in shortening like you would pie dough. Add milk and stir until moistened.
Knead dough.
Put on large 10-inch round pan and at and spread to edges of pan.
Add 1/2 cup pizza sauce or anything else you want.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh grated nutmeg.

title: harley toone's breakfast
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet, wok or Dutch oven in oil.
Add sliced pepperoni, onion and mushrooms.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add cashews and sliced olives with juice.
Season with 2 teaspoons oregano.
Cook until done, stirring occasionally.
Add diced potatoes and season with seasoned salt before stirring into cooked portion.
Cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir; reduce heat and spread cheese over top.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Melt margarine in a large casserole dish.
Cut up chicken in small pieces and put on top.
Drain vegetables and pour on top of chicken.
Mix soup and broth together and pour on top of vegetables. Do not mix.

title: strawberry-rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Combine pineapple, rhubarb and sugar in saucepan.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour into 3-pint jars and freeze.

title: aunt murrell's fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour and nutmeg.
In a cup, combine vanilla, sour cream and orange juice.
Add flour mixture and sour cream mixture alternately to butter and eggs.
Add fruit mixture to flour and butter mixture.
Blend well.
Chill dough overnight and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 325° oven until lightly brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sour cream and soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each. Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground meat into buttered baking dish.
Pour soup over it.
Spread frozen vegetables over soup.
Cover with Tater Tots. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes, butter and sugar.
Add thickening made of flour and water.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add bread cubes and stir. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chili-delux
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and seasoning.
Drain off excess fat. Add in tomato sauce and pork and beans.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or hot garlic bread.
If you like extra hot chili, add in more chili powder.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and continue to boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, quick oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Slice bread into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over bread in pan.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight or 24 hours.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serve warm with butter and syrup, powdered sugar or jam.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Whip potatoes with remaining ingredients until fluffy.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour or until set.

title: garlic lover's potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
If large, cut into thick slices.
Steam for about 7 minutes or until they are firm but slightly tender. Pour oil into a casserole dish.
Add the steamed potatoes, garlic, shallot, salt and pepper.
Toss well to mix.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir a couple of times while baking so potatoes cook evenly.
If desired, garnish with freshly chopped rosemary or parsley.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in large skillet over medium flame cook and stir sausage, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Drain cooked spaghetti and add 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in eggs quickly and add Parmesan cheese. Toss.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a heavily buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Fill pie with meat sauce; place in a preheated 350° gas oven.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over meat filling; bake an additional 5 minutes until cheese melts.
To serve, cut into wedges.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Run clams and tomatoes through food grinder.
Put in large pot and add water, salt and pepper.
Brown bacon in skillet.
Add bacon and drippings to pot.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry and season with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in large baking pan so pieces do not overlap.
Pour melted margarine or butter over chicken.
Place under broiler until brown. Watch carefully that chicken does not burn.
Remove chicken from broiler.
Combine fruit, onions, chicken broth and chili sauce. Spoon mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour or until chicken is tender in 325° or 350° oven.
Just before serving, heat Worcestershire sauce and brandy in small saucepan and pour over chicken.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all and chill.
Garnish with crumbled bacon if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put in a well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350°.
Put ketchup on top when almost done.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Soften all tortillas in chicken broth.
Place 6 tortillas in bottom of oblong pan.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, balance of chicken broth, cheese, onion and chilies.
Then layer in pan the tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade bisquick
directions: Mix well and store.
Can be used with any Bisquick recipe. Store in freezer and it's always fresh.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal with baking powder, baking soda and salt. Combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening; add to corn meal.
Add crackling (salt pork).
Heat shortening in a heavy skillet.
Drop corn mixture from tablespoons into skillet.
Brown cakes slowly on both sides.
Or bake in a greased and floured pan at 400°.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Spread 1/2 of vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom of pan.
Add butter, sugar and egg mixture, then drained pineapple, then whipped cream and nuts. Spread on other half of crumbs.
Leave in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: tenderloin tips
directions: Simmer tenderloin tips (in enough water to cover) until done; add mushrooms.
Thicken broth with cornstarch or flour; color with Kitchen Bouquet.
Add onion, celery and pepper; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice, noodles or baked potatoes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
If desired, garnish with hard-boiled egg quarters and chopped scallions. Makes 6 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a small bowl.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Knead mixture, adding more flour as needed. Roll out amount of dough needed to 1/2-inch thickness.
Using the rim of a juice glass or a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, cut out biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown, about 10 to 15 minutes, depending upon size.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl.
Allow to marinate for at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: I use the sugar-free cooked pudding.

title: chocolate covered creams
directions: Mix with electric mixer 1 box sugar, butter and milk until creamy.
Stir in second box sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Form into balls and insert flat toothpicks.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Melt paraffin in top of double boiler and add chocolate chips. Leave in double boiler while dipping the centers.
Set dipped candies on waxed paper and remove toothpicks.
Candy can be colored and flavored.

title: chocolate mints
directions: Mix all together in saucepan over low heat, stirring.
Drop small dabs on wax paper.
Allow to set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Scald milk, stir in shortening, sugar and mashed potatoes. Cool to lukewarm.
Blend well.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sauerkraut in flat dish or square Tupperware (with lid). Layer remainder of ingredients.
Do not stir.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, mix with 4 tablespoons vinegar. (You can half the recipe.)

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake 3 layers as directed and cool.

title: mom's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and oil.
Add egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: mangoes marauders beer butt chicken
directions: Wash, pat dry chicken.	Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt. Place each chicken atop one open can of beer - so can is upright in large cavity of bird.
Place beer can and chicken upright on gas grill grate.
Close lid of grill.
Cook on low heat until chicken reaches internal temperature of 180° (some beer will still be in can).

title: cheese ball
directions: Set aside 3/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Combine and mix well all ingredients.
Shape into balls (2).
Roll balls in nuts.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter.
Slowly add sugar. Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Turn into a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: pickled beets and raspberries
directions: Cut tops off beets, leaving 1 inch of stem.
Scrub beets well; trim off roots.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain and immediately place beets into ice water to stop cooking process.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, allspice, cinnamon and salt in a medium saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Divide beets and raspberries between 2 clean, hot pint jars.
Pour in the hot liquid to within 1/2 inch of the top, distributing spices equally between jars.
Wipe rims with a damp cloth; process 15 minutes in a hot water bath.
Remove and let cool.
Let stand 2 weeks before using.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
In blender, chop and blend all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: party cheese dip
directions: Blend hot sauce with cream cheese.
Blend in sour cream gradually.
Add onion soup mix and deviled ham.
Mix well and serve.

title: "dirt"(don't let the name throw you!)
directions: Remove middle from half of cookies. Grind up cookies in food processor.
Put aside.
Get extra middle and rest of cookies and grind up in processor. Put in bottom of flower pot.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Place the brisket on foil on a cookie sheet.
Pour liquid smoke over it generously.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Close tightly and place in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pie with meringue
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites with pinch of cream of tartar.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread on pie and bake at 350° until light brown.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: In a glass baking dish, spread one thin layer of dried beef. Rinse chicken with cold water and drain.
Lay chicken on top of beef and pat gently.
Mix equal parts of sour cream and mushroom soup together; brown mushrooms in butter and white wine until tender.
Disperse mushrooms through chicken around, on top, etc. Pour creamed mixture over chicken.
Top with parsley and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
No salt is needed.
Dried beef usually cooks into the chicken.
Great with rice and carrots.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place 1 teaspoon of marinade from artichokes in a saute pan.
Add the minced onion and garlic.
Saute over medium heat until onion is limp.
Chop the artichoke hearts, set aside.
In a bowl mix all remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Add the onion mixture and artichoke hearts; blend.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Done when puffed and brown.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt butter; add onion and cheese.
Add a little cheese at a time, until melted.
Add mushroom soup, then rice.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbles.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar into water.
Add frozen juices and mix well; chill.
About 30 minutes before serving, add chilled ginger ale and club soda.
Makes a tasty sparkling beverage.
(I make a half recipe and freeze to add to punch when serving.)
Serves 25; can be doubled (50) or tripled (75).

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Cream together in the bottom of a tube pan that has been well-greased, margarine and light brown sugar.
Add Karo syrup, pecans, vanilla and salt.
Add cake mix with eggs and milk instead of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: date bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Gradually add nuts.
Mix good with dates and sugar and add beaten eggs; mix all together real good.
Bake in cookie sheet for 25 or 30 minutes or until brown and cool a few minutes.
Cut into finger size shapes and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mama clara's chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute oleo, bell pepper and onion.
Add broth and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and fold in spaghetti.

title: sunrise swirl(low calorie)
directions: Combine fruit cocktail with orange concentrate and artificial sweetener.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 10 minutes.
Chill.
Layer 4 tablespoons fruit in parfait glass and 2 tablespoons yogurt for each serving.
Serves 6.
Each serving contains only 80 calories.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and almond extract until smooth and creamy.
Line bottom of square pan with thin slices of pound cake.
Pour mixture on top of pound cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm and brown.
Cool 20 minutes.
Beat sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over top of cheese cake.
Return to oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Top with blueberry, cherry, etc. pie filling and serve.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add molasses.
Sift 2 cups flour with other dry ingredients.
Add alternately to first mixture with sour milk.
Add enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut with cutter.
Put raisins in center and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Simmer,
covered,
until
thick and meat falls apart (2 hours).
Cook
uncover
last
hours.
After simmering for 2 hours,
I
usually	take
two forks and sort of shred the meat apart,
so	that it gets kind of stringy.
Sometimes I cut the meat
into	large chunks, and take one chunk at a time and put it on	a plate and shred it.
After I shred each chunk, I put it back
in
the
pot and shred another chunk, until it's all shredded;
then
let
it simmer for the remaining 3 hours.	It will
thicken
as
it
simmers.
(It makes a lot and it can be frozen.)

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Cook zucchini in boiling water that has been salted.
Cook until slightly limp; drain well. Combine eggs, cheeses, parsley and seasonings.
Spoon thin layer of spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a third of the bread crumbs; layer with a third of the zucchini, meat and cheese mixture.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix eggs and two cups of pulp together.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Mix in margarine and spices.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch glass dish and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cooked.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Add flour and stir until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Mix all together except cheese; sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy ice cream pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O in 2/3 cup boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and fruit.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 3 hours.
Garnish with whole fruit or slices. Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook for 20 minutes the rhubarb, sugar and pineapple.
Add jello.
Put into jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip pecan brownies
directions: Mix all together. (You may have to add a little more water, but batter needs to be thick, just wet enough to get it mixed.) Pat with greased hands into a 13 x 9 square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato latkes(pancakes)
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Drain liquid.
Stir in eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop a spoonful at a time into hot greased skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream and sugar or applesauce. Serves 6.

title: quick tuna salad
directions: Fix noodles as directed on bag.
Drain noodles and place in pan with soup and tuna mixture.
Let this come to a boil.
Put mixture into large bowl.
Add chow mein noodles on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease and lightly flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well until combined.
Add pumpkin, water and vinegar mixed with milk.
Beat at medium speed until combined. Mix flour with soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating at low speed.
Stir in walnuts and raisins. Divide batter between the two pans evenly.
Bake for about 70 minutes, or until bread tests done with a cake tester.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes in pans; then invert cake onto rack to cool completely.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan for about 20 or 25 minutes until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine margarine and peanut butter in a 2-quart glass bowl. Cover with a paper towel and microwave at High 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar. Press into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine morsels and shortening in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup; microwave at Medium (50% power) 2 minutes or until melted. Stir well and spread over peanut butter mixture. Cover and chill. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and oil, then stir in zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini and carrot mixture and stir in until well blended.
Add nuts.
Place in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: marinated pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large shallow dish.
Add meat; cover and refrigerate overnight, turning meat occasionally.
Next day, place meat and marinade in Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until desired degree of doneness.
To serve, slice thinly.
Yields 9 servings.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Assemble ingredients and equipment. Combine ingredients, using muffin method of mixing.
Cut into triangles, dip into mix. Deep fat fry 375° to a golden brown; these puff up and become crisp. Drain on absorbent paper. Serve with dusting of powdered sugar, syrup or honey.

title: milk toast
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; don't let burn.
Crumble loaf bread into margarine.
Add sugar or Sweet 'N Low to taste.
Add enough sweet milk to make it thick.
Heat until it starts to bubble.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and eat.

title: beef brisket in beer
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Season with salt and pepper. Place meat in 13 x 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with onion slices.
In bowl, combine chili sauce, brown sugar, garlic and beer; pour over meat.
Cover with foil.

title: everlasting salad
directions: Drain the juice of the sauerkraut and the bean sprouts.
Cut up the pepper and the celery; drain the pimentos.
Also chop up the onion.
Mix all together.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Can be kept 4 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry ground beef and drain well.
Season to taste.
Place in large casserole dish.
Top with layer of corn, then cover with potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Kid's love it with ketchup! Serves 4 to 6.

title: cottage cheese dill rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: lime-pear honey
directions: Peel and core pears and put through food chopper.
Mix all ingredients and cook approximately 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into jars; seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: blueberry syrup* * * * *
directions: Pecan pancakes are my aunt's pancake recipe to which I added pecans.
Tried it with a mix, but it wasn't very good.
At this time, we hadn't been married very long and were living in Wisconsin.

title: patty's quick 'n easy meatballs
directions: Mix well and roll into small meatballs.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, sugar and lemon juice.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Measure 1 cup syrup (add water to make cup if necessary). Add cornstarch and blend.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, butter and flavoring; cool. Place peaches in baked shell.
Pour cooled sauce over them; chill. Serve with or without cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *Cook broccoli according to directions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle some cheese on top.
May also top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts well.

title: homemade chili sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers together.
Add spices and vinegar and boil until thickens (3 to 5 hours).
Put into hot, sterilized pint or quart jars.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Breast may be cut in half, to make thinner.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Brown chicken in frying pan until it's almost cooked through.
In another skillet, saute onions and mushrooms together in a little oil, salt and pepper for taste.
Put the chicken in a sprayed baking dish, pour the onions and mushrooms on top of the chicken, then place slice of cheese on each piece.
Cover with foil and bake for about 20-30 min, Serve with favorite side dish.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Use small amount of oil in skillet to saute zucchini, onions and spices.
Line 9-inch pie plate with crescent dinner rolls. Spread mustard on top.
Fill with hot zucchini mixture.
Add beat up eggs.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Beat the butter until it is light and creamy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift the flour with the salt and baking powder.
Fold into butter mixture.
Place the dough on a cookie sheet and pat into a rectangle, 1/2-inch thick and approximately 4 x 10-inches in size.
Mark into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar and bake in center of 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut into bars and store in an airtight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add a 1/2 cup milk.
Pour in a casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top. Put back in oven and melt.

title: vegetable and chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix in butter, soup, onion, powder, pepper, vegetables and chicken; place in baking dish.
Cut biscuits in 4 pieces; place on top.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the first four ingredients. Now add 3 eggs and cream real good. Add soda, cream of tartar and flour. This is a soft dough. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken into 1/2 cup buttermilk. Roll chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Turn chicken over and bake 15 minutes more.
Turn chicken again and pour mixture of 1 cup buttermilk and mushroom soup.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a 4 quart bowl.
I use a food processor to chop all the vegetables.
Do not chop too small. Put all vegetables in liquid and let stand overnight.
It will keep up to a week in the refrigerator and will not get soggy. Great summer dish with fresh veggies.

title: "squimp" casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken in sauce
directions: Clean chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Place in baking pan (9 x 9-inch).
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fresh lemon sponge cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until whites hold soft peaks.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of the sugar, beating until whites are stiff but not dry. Transfer to another large bowl.
Put yolks in unwashed mixer bowl. Beat until thick.
Add remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating yolks very thick and ivory colored.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and water, beating until just blended.
Beat in flour at a very low speed or fold in by hand.
Add mixture to meringue, gently but thoroughly folding in with a rubber spatula.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Spread evenly.
Cut through batter with spatula several times to break any air bubbles.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tester inserted near center comes out clean. Invert on wire rack to cool.
Loosen cake from sides of pan with spatula.
Set on serving plate.
Sift powdered sugar over top if desired.
Garnish with lemon slices and leaves before serving.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix pudding, water and juice drained from pineapple and oranges.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir. Cool and add fruits.

title: breakfast sausage biscuits and gravy
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage until brown.
Drain and reserve two tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Blend in flour; brown, stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add sausage, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Serve over hot split biscuits.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill overnight and enjoy!

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Chop vegetables and drain sauerkraut.
Cover sauerkraut with water and drain again, well.
Put all ingredients together and mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Put into 2 well greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix first 7 ingredients and then gradually add flour, stirring lightly. Pour into lined muffin tins and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Makes 12+ muffins.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in large salad bowl. Mix mayonnaise, cheese and sugar.
Spread over other ingredients carefully over top to sides.
Sprinkle with bacon bits if desired.
Make the night before.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook noodles till tender.
Mix mozzarella cheese, ricotta cheese and parsley flakes all together.
Mix ground beef and Ragu sauce and cook till hot.
In a 13x9x2-inch pan spread a layer of ground beef and sauce on the bottom of pan.
Then put a layer of noodles. Then spread out layer of cheese mixture, another layer of noodles, then the rest of meat and sauce mixture on top of noodles.
Cook at 400° for 50 minutes.
Take out and spread mozzarella cheese on top and bake another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: lemon bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and pour over bread crumbs.
Add butter and let stand a few minutes.
Combine sugar, egg yolks, salt and lemon juice; add to crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
When done, top with stiffly beaten egg whites, sweetened with 1/2 cup sugar. Return to oven to brown, about 5 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat well cake mix, water, oil, Jell-O and strawberries.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back.
Flour cake tins really well.
This can also be cooked in a tube pan, then split and filled with icing.

title: waioli-room carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon
together.	Make
a well in the dry ingredients.
Add nuts,	oil,
vanilla, sugar, raisins and coconut.
Add eggs and grated
carrots.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Let stand 20 minutes before
baking.
Bake
at 350° for about
to
45 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello mix.
Add water and oil.
Blend. Add eggs one at a time.
Add half package raspberries.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with sugar, butter and half package raspberries.
Yum! Yum!

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll out.
Yields 4 pie crusts.
What part not used can be placed in wax paper and put in the freezer for your convenience.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown meat, breaking the pieces and stirring about 5 minutes. Add corn, water, tomatoes and seasonings and bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine and bake in greased casserole at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O dry (no water) with all the rest of the ingredients.
Chill.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions; let cool, then crumble. Layer all ingredients one by one into punch bowl until all ingredients are used.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1 teaspoon of sugar
