and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta with broccoli and tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes after submerging them in boiling water for 10 seconds. Cut them into pieces and set aside.
Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Cook broccoli in boiling water 3 to 4 minutes, just until tender. Put broccoli in cold water to retain color. Boil spaghetti.
While spaghetti is cooking, warm oil in skillet with garlic and red pepper flakes. When hot, add tomatoes and parsley. Stir and cook for several minutes.
When spaghetti is just about done, return the broccoli to the water to warm, then drain spaghetti and broccoli. Serve spaghetti and broccoli with tomato mixture and Parmesan cheese on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great served with a loaf of sourdough bread.
Scoop out the center of the loaf of bread and cut into small pieces.
Fill the middle of the loaf with dip and eat with the bread pieces.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat.
Drain. Stir in sauce and pasta. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine egg, Ricotta and Mozzarella.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread half of the pasta mixture; layer cheese mixture over all. Top with remaining pasta. Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes. Top with Romano. Bake until cheese melts.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Brown ground beef (drain).
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion. Set aside.
Mix biscuit mix and water to form a soft dough. Pat in pan, pressing 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan. Spoon sour cream mixture over top. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp pinwheel sandwiches
directions: Add shrimp to food processor with mayonnaise, lemon juice, sherry, salt and pepper; puree until smooth.
Transfer to small bowl and stir in parsley.
Trim crusts from bread.
Place 2 slices end to end, overlapping 1/2 inch.
With rolling pin, roll bread into a very thin, 7 x 4-inch rectangle; spread lightly with butter and then with 2 tablespoons shrimp puree.
Roll bread up tightly from 4-inch side, jelly roll fashion.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Repeat with remaining bread.
To serve, slice thin and arrange on trays.

title: condensed milk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix eggs in separate bowl.
Add in butter and milk.
Mix in flour slowly.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Leave a little flour to pour over the nuts.
Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Pour into tube pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand until cool.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Mandarin oranges, eggs and oil together for 20 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until transparent. Combine beans and onion; put in casserole dish.
Stir catsup and brown sugar together; pour over beans.
Sprinkle bacon over top. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and salt; add 1 1/2 cups flour. Use one cup flour on nuts and fruit, then add to mixture with vanilla.
Mix well; roll into balls and bake 15 or 18 minutes on cookie sheets in a 325° oven.

title: my own harvest pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine yolks, oil and milk with dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Fold in egg whites. Cook on hot griddle.

title: pig-in-a-blanket meal
directions: Preheat oven
to
Combine first four ingredients in a large
skillet
and cook until sausage browns.
Add mushrooms, stir and drain everything; set aside.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic; drain.
Saute zucchini until tender; combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Put cheese on top; bake until melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk; fold in eggs and add chopped walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Blend pudding, milk and powdered sugar until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan (or spray with Pam).
Line with graham crackers.
Spread with pudding-Cool Whip mixture.
Top with crackers, pudding and crackers, until mixture is used up. Finish with crackers.
Spread icing on last layer of crackers. Add nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
and pour in buttered casserole dish. Top with Rice Krispies and 1/2 stick butter.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: spiced apple juice
directions: Heat to boiling, but do not boil.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Mix above and pour over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 300° or 350°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix as you would a cake.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Fill when cool with Whoopie Pie Filling.

title: white bread pudding
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish; line bottom with toasted bread cubes.
Sprinkle raisins and pecans over bread cubes.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; add milk, eggs, hot water and vanilla. Pour over bread mixture in baking dish and bake at 375° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake in oven 350 degrees for 30 minutes, top with crackers and butter and return to oven for another 20 minutes (until golden brown and bubbly).

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Combine all in a large bowl.
Cover.
Put in icebox for about 24 hours.

title: hot sausage and shrimp jambalaya
directions: Put sausage in a large heavy iron skillet and cook.
Add onion and cook until onion is clear.
Add parsley and garlic.
Cook until parsley is limp.
Add water for tomatoes (mashed with spoon), thyme and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and shrimp. Stir and cover.
Cook on low heat.
Stir often and lift rice with fork.
Add more liquid if needed (1/2 cup).
Cook 30 minutes or until rice grains are tender and separate easily.

title: greek salad
directions: Marinate for 1 hour.
Just before serving, toss lightly with 1 head of romaine lettuce (torn into bite size pieces).

title: plum cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze or spread with Cream Cheese Icing.
Good holiday dessert!

title: jello salad
directions: For first layer, dissolve black cherry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and add drained Mandarin oranges.
Pour into jello mold and chill until firm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and cream butter/margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add flour, about 1 cup at a time, and beat well each time, scraping sides of bowl.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: banana apricot mousse
directions: Puree all ingredients in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Spoon into 4 dessert dishes.
Chill well before serving.

title: light sherbet dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and crushed shortbread.
Spread half on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Add layers of sherbet.
Top with remaining shortbread mix.
Save a few crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Freeze overnight.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk, pineapple and a couple cans of Orange Crush together; pour into ice cream freezer.
Pour remaining Orange Crush into ice cream freezer.
Pack with ice and salt.
Mix until frozen.

title: chex b.b.q.  mix
directions: Stir together cereals, pretzels, crackers and peanuts in a large microwaveable bowl; set aside. Stir together remaining ingredients until blended. Pour over cereal mixture in bowl, stirring until evenly coated. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Spread on aluminum foil or paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef and rice.
Stir in salt, black pepper, celery salt, green pepper, grated onion and garlic.
Form into 18 small meat balls.
Pour tomato juice into large skillet.
Add cloves, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Mix well and add meat balls. Cover and simmer over low heat 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender throughout.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Cook and drain ground beef for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add water and sauce to beef.
Mix egg and cottage cheese or Ricotta cheese

title: rum cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan with Crisco.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: With a fork or pastry blender, crush half of strawberries. Stir in cornstarch and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until clear and thickened.
Cool.
Slice rest of strawberries into halves and fold into cooled mixture.
Turn into baked crust. Refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: scarlet o'hara cocktail
directions: In a blender, add ingredients.
Blend well and serve.

title: texas pie(because it's bigger and better)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into 10-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Easy and delicious!

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine all ingredients; press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool completely.

title: broccoli, rice & cheese casserole
directions: Slice raw cabbage in about 3/4 to 1 inch slices.
Cook on top of stove until fork tender. Drain. Place in casserole.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover pickles in water for 3 hours.
Turn once during 3 hours. Squeeze out.
Drain.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, then jar.
Makes 6 1/2 pints.

title: cherry o'cream cheese pie(todd's favorite pie)
directions: Whip the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk while whipping. Continue whipping, adding lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Pour pie filling on top.
Serve.

title: cheese christmas tree
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; press out on tray and form "tree."

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream together cream cheese, olives, chilies and Tabasco sauce. Spread approximately 2 tablespoons onto a tortilla and roll jelly-roll fashion and roll in plastic wrap and chill.
Before serving, cut into 3/8-inch wide pieces and serve with salsa for dipping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Oil and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in batter and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash and mix all ingredients (can be made the night before).
Bake at 350° for 45 -60 minutes till heated through.
Leftovers will last up to two weeks.
However, they won't be around that long.
Delicious!

title: face lift breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Gently stir in cheese, sausage and bread.
Place in buttered 9 x 13 dish. Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours. Place in cold oven. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sweet rolls or toasted English muffins.

title: two lemon chess pies
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salts, cereal, eggs and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Combine remaining ingredients in a skillet and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place meatballs in sauce and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Yields 65 meatballs.

title: deep, dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water; batter will be runny.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with your favorite icing or powdered sugar.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Chop hearts, mix with rest of ingredients and chill well. Serve with crackers.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Mix well (mix will be crumbly).
Form into 1-inch balls.
Put in refrigerator overnight on waxed paper.

title: stephie stuff
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Add mushroom soup; stir in cheese until blended in.
Then lay Tater Tots on top and cover complete package of Tater Tots.
Put in oven at 350° until bubbles around the pan.
Then take out.
Feeds 8 to 10 people.

title: sweet potato casserole(simply delicious)
directions: Bake sweet potatoes and mash.
Mix in sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube pan.
Put pecans on bottom to cover well.
Place rolls on top of nuts.
Pour dry pudding mix next, brown sugar over pudding, then cover with pecans.
Melt butter.
Pour over pecans. Put wax paper on top and a towel.
Let rise overnight on countertop.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar, mixing well.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: crawfish pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Saute onion in a little butter.
Prepare gravy mix according to package.
Mix crawfish, potatoes, vegetables and onions together with gravy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover top with second pie crust.
Cut a few slits in top of crust.
Flute edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let sit for 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop the onion and pepper.
Mix and put in 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 300° for about 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan, preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
In greased baking dish, put about 1/2 cup sauce, spread noodles to cover.
Add cheese mix and some sauce.
Repeat with noodles, cheese mix and sauce.
(You can make as high as you wish.)
Top with the remaining 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour hot water around edge, cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting so it gets a bit firm.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
Cover with water.
Boil potatoes until they are almost done.
Make crust and line the pan. Dip potatoes out of the water; put them in the pan.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in 2-quart saucepan until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Add enough water, if necessary, to reserved clam liquid, to measure 1 cup.
Stir clams, liquid, potato, salt and pepper into onion mixture.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and boil until potato is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat, stirring occasionally, just until hot (do not boil).
Yields 4 servings, 240 calories per serving.

title: good old potato soup(instead of just potatoes for supper, why not try potato soup?)
directions: Cook onions and potatoes in boiling water until they are very tender.
Save 1 cup of potato water.
Run the cooked vegetables through a sieve.
Blend flour, butter, salt and pepper and add potato water.
Cook well.
Add milk and sieved vegetables.
If necessary, beat three minutes with an eggbeater to get well blended.
Cook 15 minutes and serve hot.
Serve with crackers. Serves 4.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chips and condensed milk together in a double boiler or microwave.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Spread it on a greased 9-inch square dish.
Chill about 2 hours.
Cut into small squares. Very rich. Makes 2 pounds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and chop into bite-size pieces. Heat soup and canned milk together.
Melt butter together with 1 cup chicken broth.
Mix all with cornbread stuffing mix, including the packet that comes with the stuffing mix.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6-8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Last 5 minutes put can of Durkee dried onion rings on top and brown.

title: sasquatch
directions: Cut corn from cobs.
Melt oleo in skillet over medium heat and saute onion.
Add corn, then zucchini.
Cook, covered, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: california potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, soup, 1/4 cup melted butter, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well. Add this mixture to the hash browns. Spread in large buttered casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Top with corn flake crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with peanut butter. While still hot add marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: brazil cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Combine soda, salt and flour together.
Put coconut, candied cherries and Brazil nuts into the mixture and mix well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs and beat well with a wooden spoon or for 3 minutes with a mixer. Stir in the orange juice, bananas and walnuts. Add the baking soda to the flour and blend well, then stir into the wet ingredients. Bake at 350° in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour or
until done.

title: sub-lime loaf
directions: Brown coconut in butter until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add the cracker crumbs and mix well.
Press 1/2 of the mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in hot water; stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thick. Fold in whipped milk.
Spoon into pan.
Top with remaining crumbs. Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping and a cherry. Excellent.
Serves 8.

title: chicken in soup
directions: Mix together in baking dish and cook in oven 2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in hot oil.
Add garlic, onion, tomatoes and wine.
Cover and simmer over low heat, about 30 minutes until thickest pieces are tender.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put sauerkraut over each chicken breast.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours covered with foil.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with Thousand Island dressing on the side. Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips with wax.
Mix margarine, peanut butter and Rice Krispies together, using hands. Make into small balls.
Dip into chocolate mixture and set on wax paper.
Place wax paper between layers when storing.
Makes 13 dozen.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Heat pan.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and ginger.
Add pork mixture and stir-fry. Again heat 2 tablespoons oil and ginger.
Add salt and celery and stir-fry.
Add cabbage and stir-fry.
Put in colander and cover with a weight and let drain.
Wrap rolls and deep-fry.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening until shortening is well crumbled.
Mix beaten egg, water and vinegar together.
Add to flour mixture.
This can be rolled out and used now or kept in the freezer and used as needed.

title: cocktail party cheese cookies
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and cheese into a dough with your hands.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix peanuts, pretzels, cereals and M&M's in large bowl.
Melt chocolate or coating in double boiler or in microwave (don't burn!) as directed on package.
Stir.

title: every day meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Top with Piquant Sauce (following).
Put in shallow loaf pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Better if it sits a while before eating.

title: raisin-walnut meringue pie
directions: In a double boiler, combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Blend in egg yolks.
Add sour cream, raisins and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick. Cool. Add walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Add cream of tartar.
Beat until peaks begin to form. Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy. Put meringue on pie. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until delicately browned.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry ice cream
directions: Place the first four ingredients into a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches a boil; then lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
In a 2-quart ice cream freezer can, pour the Eagle Brand, half and half, vanilla and salt.
Whip the whipping cream and gently fold into the mixture. Add blueberry mixture and enough milk to fill the container.

title: fajitas
directions: Mix and marinade at least 1 hour.

title: navy bean salad
directions: Boil beans until mushy.
Add remaining ingredients and serve on lettuce.

title: aunt deb's easy lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions. While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef in large skillet; drain. Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef. Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer as follows: Noodles, cottage cheese, ground beef mixture, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese, noodles, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese. Mushrooms may be added if desired. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove, drain and break into pieces.
Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until tender and golden brown.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Cook on low, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in water and vinegar.
Heat mixture to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add crumbled bacon and cooked potatoes into hot mixture.
Heat through, stirring lightly to coat potatoes.
(If desired, salad can be warmed in crock-pot for several hours.)

title: date nut chewies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Drop by tablespoons an inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool pans on wire rack.
Remove cookies with spatula.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Pour over lime jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese until melts.
Add crushed pineapple.
Blend Cool Whip and mayonnaise and add to mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Wash roast; trim off excess fat.
With small knife, pierce 3 to 5 times.
Insert 1/2 garlic clove in each place.
Sprinkle top and sides with seasoned salt to taste.
Lightly sprinkle with sage (top and sides).
Insert meat thermometer and cook at 325° for 1 3/4 to 2 1/2 hours or until thermometer registers desired doneness, 140° for rare, 165° for medium and 180° for done.

title: fast night cakes
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add softened margarine.
Gradually add very hot tap water and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl often.
Add egg and 1/2 cup of flour to make a thick batter. Beat on high 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise 1 hour in draft-free area until double. Turn dough out on floured board, knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Roll out to 8 x 16-inch rectangle.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Cut a slit 1/4-inch deep in each square.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Fry in deep hot oil at 375° until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 32 doughnuts.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease 2 quart casserole.
Into mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in caraway seeds.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until coarse.
Stir in raisins. Combine buttermilk, egg and soda; stir into flour until just moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth; shape into ball.
Place in casserole 4 inches deep in center.
Brush with beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach pieces. Boil eggs; fry bacon crisp. Combine oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion as a dressing. Refrigerate.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce (not wet); break up.
Layer in large flat bowl the lettuce, celery, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle peas over top.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar on top, then cheese and bacon last.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Press salad down to get cover on if necessary.

title: sweet broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Add peanuts and raisins.
Stir in broccoli.
Chill well.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir soup and 1/2 of oleo together.
Add Veg-All and 1/2 of Ritz crackers.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle rest of crackers (mixed with rest of oleo) on top.
Sprinkle a little grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Heat about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello and apricot nectar; heat until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate 3 hours.
When set, add topping.

title: coconut pecan layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round pans.
Beat flour, sugar, shortening, buttermilk, egg yolks and vanilla, in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Beat in egg whites, high 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until cake top springs back when touched.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove to racks, cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese pecan frosting.

title: microwave orange-spiced chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast in half;
place skin side up in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Top	with onions.
Sprinkle salt, paprika and pepper.
Mix orange
juice,
brown	sugar, vinegar, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour
over
chicken.
Cover
tightly.
Microwave. Turn dish half turn.
Cover 8 to 13 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, salt, pepper, pimientos, cheese and butter; mix together.
Add corn with liquid; mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cook oats in water and cool.
Beat eggs with mixer. Add oats. Add
melted
margarine, then add both sugars. Mix well. Add
all dry
ingredients.
Pour
in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: capellini with shrimp and herb sauce
directions: Cook capellini until barely tender, drain, rinse and place in large bowl.
Toss capellini with little olive oil to keep from sticking together.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of olive oil and melt the butter over medium heat; add shrimp and garlic and saute until shrimp just turns pink.
Stir in lemon juice, basil, parsley, oregano, dill weed and chicken broth; reduce the heat and simmer until heated through.
Pour the shrimp mixture over the capellini and toss gently until the capellini is lightly coated.
Season with pepper and serve.

title: spicy hot cross buns
directions: In a small bowl, proof the yeast in 1/2 c. warm water for 15 minutes.

In a food processor, blend 1-1/2 c. flour with the yeast mixture, potatoes, milk, butter, eggs, salt, brown sugar, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, mace and cloves, pulsing 5 times. Transfer the mixture to a bowl and let stand, covered, for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Meanwhile, let the raisins soften 30 minutes in the heated rum/water mixture. Into the yeast mixture, stir the raisins with the rum, citron and 4-1/2 c. of remaining flour.
Combine until a dough is formed.
Knead in the remaining flour and then let rise until doubled.
Punch down and form into 20 balls.
Place the balls 1 inch apart on a greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30-40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15-18 minutes, or until golden.
Glaze:
In
a small saucepan, combine the milk and sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until it is reduced to 1/4 c.
Brush the buns with the glaze while they are warm, and then brush them again 2 minutes later (giving the first layer a chance to set).
Cool completely. Icing:
In a small bowl beat together the butter, milk and lemon juice.
Add the powdered sugar in batches, beating until smooth after each addition.
Put into a pastry bag fitted with a small, plain tip, and pipe the icing onto each bun in the form of a cross.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Blend in pretzels.
Pack in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Mix 3 tablespoons of sugar and cream cheese and spread over first layer.
Mix Jell-O and water, then add strawberries and let begin to cool.
Pour over top and chill completely.

title: icy fruit punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, 1 cup water, 1 cup sugar and Kool-aid; all but pineapple juice.
Add pineapple juice and all the rest of ingredients to 1 gallon of water.
Freeze in gallon containers (Tupperware or empty plastic milk container).
Leave space to freeze at top to expand while freezing.
Can be done far ahead for parties or weddings.

title: sour cream drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Spread with Maple Butter Glaze.

title: goldwater beans
directions: Cook beans fast for 1 1/2 hours.
Brown meat and add onion, bell pepper, seasonings and green chilies. Cook until mixed well. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add to beans. Stir in tomatoes and simmer for 4 to 6 hours.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Grind and drain onion, green peppers, red bell peppers and tomatoes.
Add flour, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and celery seed.
Cook all ingredients together for 30 minutes. Remove from heat. Add last, 1-quart mayonnaise to the cooked ingredients and mix well. Seal in hot sterile jars (pint).

title: sweet freezer pickles
directions: Let cucumbers and onion stand in 2 tablespoons salt for 2 hours.
Pack into sterile jars.
Heat sugar and vinegar just enough to melt sugar.
Pour over pickles; seal and freeze.
White vinegar must be used.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine bread cubes, chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Trim the
slices
of bread and lay on top. Combine eggs and
milk
and
pour
over bread. Spoon soup over this.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, putting cheese on top the last 15 minutes. Cut in squares and serve.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry the chicken.
Melt margarine.
Add garlic and oregano.
On paper towel, mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Dip chicken in margarine mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs and cheese.
Place in large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour remaining margarine on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients according to directions on cake mix box.

title: broccoli and tomato fettucine
directions: Cook and stir broccoli in dressing for 2 minutes.
Cook tomatoes in small saucepan over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over fettucine.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
first
five
ingredients together.
Gently stir in broccoli and
put the mixture into a casserole dish.
Melt the margarine and
add the cornbread stuffing.	Mix and pour it on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This is a very tasty vegetable dish and always a sellout!

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first four ingredients. Mix well. Form into a ball & roll in chopped nuts.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease baking sheet.
Unroll pizza dough and cut into squares, separating on baking sheet.
Spoon pizza sauce on squares.
Spread and top with pepperoni, olives and peppers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice first.
Then add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: bacon burgers
directions: Shape ground beef into patties.
Wrap each with a strip of bacon, secure with a toothpick and broil to desired doneness. Remove toothpick and serve on warm open-faced buns.
Top with your favorite gravy.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble with lettuce, cauliflower and onion. Spread Miracle Whip over this and add cheese.
Do not mix.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.
Mix lightly and add salt to taste.

title: humus
directions: Blend it all gradually and correct seasonings to your taste. If you need to add a bit of reserved liquid to make it blend, do so.
Excellent with veggies or crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies(no flour needed!)
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and shape dough into balls (small).
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot stroganoff
directions: In a large crock-pot, combine beef, chopped onion, 2 to 3 cans of soup, 1 envelope of dry onion soup mix and sliced mushrooms. Mix thoroughly.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then low for 4 or more hours.
Serve over cooked noodles or white rice.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage into glass bowl.
Stir in salt and ice cubes. Cover.
Let stand 1 hour.
After hour, squeeze out cabbage and put into glass or enameled container.
Add carrot, pepper and onion. In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water, celery and mustard seed.
Let come to boil, remove from heat.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and put into freezer container.
Will keep as long as 1 year.
Yield depends on size of cabbage.
(This is a good way to use up garden cabbage.)
Let thaw in refrigerator.

title: bootleg beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry until half done.
Add chopped onion.
Pour off most grease and add pork and beans.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and cover.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or bake slowly at 300° for a couple of hours.

title: raspberry divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water together over moderate heat until it reaches the hard ball stage (252°) by candy thermometer, stirring often.
Beat egg whites until foamy, then add the gelatin.
Continue beating until egg whites stand in peaks, then slowly beat in the hot syrup mixture.
Continue beating until test spoonful will hold its shape.
Add nuts; drop quickly onto waxed paper, or pour out onto greased dish.
Cut into pieces.

title: custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt; pour scalded milk into eggs, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Stir in vanilla.
Makes 12 servings.

title: casserole ole
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and add a little bean juice. Add cumin, garlic powder and chili powder.
Layer meat mixture, rice and pinto beans in a greased casserole dish.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump can of pineapple in the bottom (juice and all), then spread pie filling on top of that. Sprinkle cake mix on top of the pie filling.
Put the margarine on the very top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach soup
directions: Make a white sauce by combining shortening, flour and milk. Add cooked spinach and cheese. Stir constantly until cheese melts. If you would like a more liquid soup, add more milk.

title: ma's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate baking powder and flour with milk.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Grease and flour pan.

title: frontier dinner
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and chill in cold water.
Heat chili and tomato soup in a large skillet. Blend in the chilled and drained macaroni.
Stir until mixture is heated throughout.
Just as good reheated.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine honey and peanut butter in a saucepan and cook on low heat until peanut butter melts.
Add dry milk and chocolate, stirring until chocolate melts.
Add remaining ingredients and spread mixture in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Rinse and chop the broccoli.
Use only the tips of the broccoli (not the stems).
Chop the onion and nuts; add raisins. In a bowl, mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
This sauce should then be stirred into the larger bowl of other ingredients. Sprinkle cooked and crumbled bacon on the top of the salad before serving.
Salad can be made ahead of time and is better after chilling for a few hours.
Keeps well overnight.
Stir before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheesy onion stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Remove stems from mushrooms; discard stems.
Fill caps with cream cheese.
Broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, then add apples, oleo and nuts.
Add together and mix by hand (no mixer).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Spoon into graham cracker pie crust.
Cool before serving.

title: taco salad spread
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sour cream and salt.
Spread evenly on platter.
Layer on top the lettuce, tomato, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Pour taco sauce over all.
Serve with taco chips.

title: grape ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and juices; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and cool.
Pour gelatin and remaining ingredients into freezer can.
Add enough milk to reach fill line. Freeze.
Preparation Time:
45 minutes plus freezing time. Yield:
1 gallon.

title: jane's summer salad
directions: Stir ingredients together and you have a great summer salad. Salads are at their best when lettuce has been spun with a salad spinner to remove moisture or pat-dry the leaves with a paper towel.

title: venison with spring onions
directions: Spread mustard lightly over each piece of cubed venison. Place whole spring onion in middle and roll.
Keep mustard inside the roll.
Tie meat with string or fasten with toothpicks.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dust roll-ups lightly with flour and brown in oil.
Remove and make gravy.
Place meat back into gravy.
Add bouillon cubes.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Mix.
Spread over first layer and top with Cool Whip.
Toasted coconut can be sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and egg yolks and cook a few minutes longer.
When done, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: bublanina(blueberry cake)
directions: Cream butter well, add sugar and cream well.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons egg whites and 3 tablespoons flour into batter-sugar mixture. Alternate until all whites and flour are incorporated.
Put in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skin from grapes.
Bring pulp from grapes to a boil. Press through a sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins to pulp mixture. Mix sugar, flour, salt and lemon peel and add to grapes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with latticework of crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
If using pink or white grapes, do not add any lemon to mixture.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 30 minutes or until tender. Drain; let cool.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside. Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients in large bowl. Gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons butter and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal coconut muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a bowl.
Allow to soak 30 minutes.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
Blend together melted shortening, brown sugar, egg and coconut; add oatmeal mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in dry ingredients, just enough to mix together.
Spoon into muffin tins, well-greased, or use cupcake papers.
Reserve some batter.
With small spoon, put a small dab of preserves on each muffin, then cover each with remaining dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together pumpkin, Cool Whip, instant pudding (dry) and pumpkin pie spices.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows and pecans.
Takes about 3 minutes to mix.
Very popular at holidays.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Melt the butter; stir in flour and chopped pecans.
Press into bottom of a large Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Take jar and fill with small cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and pickling spice; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour over cucumbers, packed.
Seal jar.

title: baked eggs(breakfast goodie)
directions: Place bread on bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan. Cube cheese and put on bread. Combine eggs and seasonings. Pour over bread and cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Fry bacon crisp and crumble over the top. Serves 10 to 12.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: chili jackpot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute meat, green pepper and onion in skillet sprayed with cooking spray.
Add salt, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well. Add tomato sauce, cooked macaroni, beans and half of cheese.
Mix well to blend.
Pour into 2-quart casserole sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jean's cookies
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients together with electric mixer and then add last 4 ingredients, mixing by hand.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Cookies will be a light color when done.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken by covering with water and boil until tender when stuck with a fork.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add chicken broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream and wine.
Place broccoli crosswise in 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over it.
Top with chicken.

title: mushrooms with tomatoes(funghi con pomodori)
directions: Wash
mushrooms
thoroughly.
Cut
in
half and bring 1 quart of salted water to a boil.
Boil mushrooms about 3 to 4 minutes. Saute garlic in oil until brown.
Discard garlic and saute mushrooms
for
about
10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, hot pepper and parsley.
Cook an additional 30 minutes on medium low heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Place onions in bottom of slow cooker.
Add meat.
Top with carrots and celery and cover with tomatoes.
Cover.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 3 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice, but why not my mashed potatoes, as Taylor enjoys?
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt together, then stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (glass pan preferred).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients in small saucepan over medium heat until thickened.
Reduce heat.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes to blend flavors. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: double decker mocha
directions: Note:
Another chocolate pudding can be substituted for the coffee pudding.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Put apples into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon mixed with sugar.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots until soft; puree in food processor.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting knife; if it comes out clean,
it is done.
Check every few minutes after 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken stuffed bundles
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion and parsley flakes and set aside.
In a large saucepan, prepare gravy by mixing together chicken broth, creamy chicken mushroom soup, minced onion, and sweet pepper flakes; warm over low heat.
In a bowl, prepare dough by combining the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt; mix well. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in water; knead gently.
Roll dough into 1/8 inch thickness; cut into six squares.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture in the center of each square. Fold dough over and press edges together firmly to seal.
Drop bundles into simmering gravy. Cover and cook over medium heat 15-20 minutes or until pastry flakes.
Serves 2-3.

title: easy homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute onions in 1 tbsp. of margarine. Add ground beef and cook over medium heat stirring until brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat for at least 45 minutes to one hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomatoes into mixture until covered.
Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Fry tomatoes in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Serves 6.

title: lazy day cool whip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Put sugar in a pan (do not use Teflon).
Add water; stir and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat so that mixture boils, but not furiously.
Stir constantly until mixture forms a ball in cold water.
Add pecans, stirring gently.
Stir until evaporation reduces the liquid to zero and pecans crust.
Sprinkle vanilla over pecans.
Stir until pan and pecans are dry.
Spread pecans on a cold cookie sheet and let the mixture cool.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: dip for tortilla chips
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread in bottom of glass 9-inch pie pan. Spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: granny cotton's applesauce bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with the oil, then add applesauce. Pour into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Drain pineapple and put on top of cake.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with cream cheese until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk and pudding; beat until thick.
Spread over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O until it starts setting.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Ready to serve as soon as congealed.
Keeps well for a week.

title: quick camp stew
directions: Cube and cook potatoes.
Chop onion.
Break meats into pieces. Add all ingredients.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add water if necessary.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Mix and freeze at least 24 hours.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Blend in flour
and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into small balls. Roll in 10x sugar.
Press with thumb.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi recipe chicken
directions: Cook chicken breast on grill, basting often with this mixture. Be sure to cook slowly.

title: scallop stir-fry
directions: Pour sesame and peanut oils around top of a preheated wok, coating sides.
Add scallops; cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms and next 4 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes, or until tender.

title: budget casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, adding any seasonings you prefer (i.e.: garlic, celery, salt, pepper, etc.)
Mix all other ingredients in large ovensafe casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle a little more Cheddar cheese on top if you prefer and enjoy.
This recipe can be cut in half if too large.
This recipe feeds 8 hungry adults.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, shortening, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in milk.
Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef and vegetables.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Cover with shredded cheese.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: In a small bowl, combine margarine, apricot spread, salt, orange rind, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Place carrots in a medium saucepan. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat, covered, 2 minutes. Drain.
Place in a serving bowl. Spoon sauce over carrots. Toss and serve.

title: oh so good cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add egg and vanilla.
Add remaining dry ingredients, leaving chips to the last.
Drop or roll in hand.
Bake at 350°F for 6-8 min.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Add beaten egg to canned milk.
Mix with margarine and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add nuts, coconut, and crushed crackers to mixture and pour over whole crackers.
Put a layer of whole crackers on top.

title: copenhagen cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Blend in tomato sauce and salt.
Put 2 cups cabbage in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 meat sauce.
Add remaining cabbage and pour sauce over top. Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: noodle and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Beat the sugar, oleo and peanut butter together.
Shape into balls shaped as eggs.
Dip in the following:
Melt the chocolate chips or butterscotch chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in it.
Drain on foil until set.

title: french chocolate squares(best ever brownies)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
In separate bowl, beat eggs; add salt and sugar.
Mix in melted butter and chocolate. Stir in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 7-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in square comes out clean.
I usually double this recipe.
May be kept in freezer for unplanned treats.

title: caramel pies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Stir over medium heat until coconut is toasted.
Mix together cream cheese, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of cream cheese mixture in bottom of both pie shells.
Add 1/2 of coconut and pecan mixture to this.
Drizzle 1/2 jar of caramel topping.
Repeat layers, ending with caramel topping.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate ice cream butterscotch dessert(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar; cut in butter.
This mix should make coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Put mix on cookie sheet and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (until golden brown). Stir while still warm to crumble; cool mix.
Spread half of crumbs in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Drizzle half of sauce over crumbs, then spoon softened ice cream over mix (using all of it).
Top with last half of crumbs and sauce.
Place in freezer for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: italian herb seasoned vegetables
directions: In sauce pan over medium high heat, bring broth, garlic powder and vegetable to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetable are tender- crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sour cream chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk, sour cream and sugar.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with whipped topping; sprinkle chopped nuts over topping.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potatoes and apple bake(murrell's)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and slice.
Make syrup of sugar, flour, water, butter, salt and apple pie spice.
Alternate layers of potatoes, apples, raisins and syrup until all are used. Place in a 350° oven until mixture bubbles; cool slightly. Arrange marshmallows on top.
Return to oven to brown.

title: tampa tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea; let stand 3 minutes.
Remove bags.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add ice water and fruit juices.
Pour into ice-filled glasses and serve.
If desired, garnish with lime slices and fresh cherries.

title: veggie bites
directions: Finely chop broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, green pepper and tomato.
Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, pinching edges together to seal.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Let cool.

title: party potatoes
directions: Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Place sliced pineapple and cherries on top.
Beat 3 egg yolks; add sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and pineapple juice.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites.
Pour over pineapple and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, then turn out on cookie sheet.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make orange juice and pink lemonade to directions on can.
Mix both together with 7-Up.
Add bananas, cherries and pineapple. This punch can be served as stated or with the gin and vodka.

title: tommie's mock chocolate eclair
directions: Spread graham crackers (left whole) in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: hot chicken salad(6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and bacon.
Place in ungreased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with bacon.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt brown sugar, butter and water together; then bring to boil until soft ball stage (238°) on candy thermometer.
Pour over corn and stir, let cool a little.
Rub butter on hands and form mixture into balls.

title: deep fried shrimp
directions: Wash and clean shrimp.
Mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper and paprika in mixing bowl.
In a bag, put flour and Bay seasoning together.
Dip shrimp in the mixture by putting the shrimp in a bag.
Put shrimp in frying pan with grease and deep fry.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add with sugar.
Put into refrigerator overnight.
The next day, add other ingredients and keep cold.

title: low tide chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Saute garlic in oil. Flour chicken and lightly fry, then place in a roasting pan. Strain oil, saving approximately 1/4 cup.
Pour oil back into pan and add the water, bouillon cubes, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook on high heat until water has almost boiled away.
Then add mushrooms.
Saute over a low flame for 10 minutes.
Cook spinach until done, and drain, then put over chicken.
Pour mushrooms and sauce over chicken.
Place chicken in oven at 350° for 10 minutes and serve over rice.
It will look like low tide on the beach if done correctly!

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Add Veg-All, cream of potato soup, cream of chicken soup
and cooked and diced chicken.
Pour half of mixture into first pie shell.
Cover with other pie shell.
(Makes 2 pies).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can freeze other chicken pot pie until later.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add milk and butter to sugar and bring to full boil.
(Can bring to full boil in microwave, too.)
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oats.
Stir until mixture starts to firm, then drop onto buttered dish with teaspoon or pour into buttered cookie sheet and cut into squares when cooled.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
After it cools, mix next 3 ingredients.
Whip and spread over crust.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Mix strawberries into jello.
Will form a gel.
Spread over middle layer.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Butter bread; cube and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese, sausage or hamburger, red pepper and onions in order over the bread.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in hot oil; add meat and seasonings.
Brown lightly.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add soups (no water); cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Combine sauce and spaghetti before serving.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt together butter, oil, mini marshmallows, vanilla and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered angel food pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wet hands and press in firmly. Cover and refrigerate until ready to slice and serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown round steak.
Add water and steak mix.
Can use mushrooms and water chestnuts.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight; serve with veggies.

title: clingons
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large microwave bowl, microwave 4 cups marshmallows, peanut butter and margarine on High for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.

title: easter egg bread
directions: About five
hours
before serving:
In bowl, mix sugar, salt, yeast and
1 cup flour.
Heat butter and milk until very warm (125°).
With
mixer
at
low speed, beat liquid into dry ingredients.
At medium speed, beat two more minutes.
Beat in 2 eggs, 1 egg white and 3/4 cup flour; beat two minutes.
Stir in lemon peel and 1 1/4 cups flour.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and season if you wish.
Wire whisk cream soup. In 9 x 13-inch pan, add cooked beef; drain off fat.
Pour cream soup over beef.
Smooth out with a spoon.
All of beef will not be covered.
Sprinkle cheeses over beef and soup.
Cover with Tater Tots, side by side, until cheese is covered.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
These can be frozen uncooked.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Melt butter; cream cheese should be soft.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cookie crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Start with crust in a 13x9-inch glass dish; add graham cracker and oleo, cool.

title: english rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk; mix well.
Pour batter over nuts and fruit; mix thoroughly.
Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy pinto beans and sausage
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine beans, salt, pepper and sliced jalapenos.
Cook 3 to 4 hours, until beans are tender, adding water as needed.
Brown sausage; drain.
Combine with beans and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until ready to eat.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold instant pudding mix into whipped topping.
Add remaining ingredients and fold together.
Chill.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons mix in 1 cup of hot water.

title: noodles and cabbage with onion
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion.
Melt butter in a large skillet. When it is hot, stir in onion, cabbage, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes or until onion and cabbage are softened.
While onion and cabbage are cooking, cook noodles in lightly salted boiling water as package directs.
Drain well.
Sprinkle cabbage with a few drops of vinegar and toss to combine.
Add noodles to skillet and mix.
Continue to cook, stirring until heated through.
Tastes great as a side dish with smoked meats.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add salad dressing, water, vanilla and soda.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: dill crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients, but crackers, in deep bowl with lid. Then add crackers and let set overnight.
Stir often.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Best toasted.

title: sausage roll
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown crumbled sausage with the onion and drain off all fat.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add milk and stir just to mix.
Knead lightly a few times.
Roll into a rectangle on a lightly floured surface. Spread with reserved sausage and then cheese.
Roll up from the long side; tuck ends under and place on a greased baking sheet, seam side down.
Bake about 20 minutes until browned.
Cool slightly before slicing.
Good warm or at room temperature.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and leave for 45 minutes, then brown.
Bake chicken 1 hour at 350°; turn only once, then pour sauce over chicken.
Bake approximately 1 hour, covered.
To fry chicken, brown in skillet on both sides; drain fat, then pour sauce over chicken.
Turn once.
Fry approximately 15 minutes, covered.

title: peanut butter reese's bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the last two ingredients in pan on top of stove; stir until glossy.
Pour on top of dry mixture.
Spread evenly over top.
Chill until solid.
Cut into squares.

title: hot crab meat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds, mixing until well blended.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and serve hot with cold, crisp pieces of raw vegetables or crackers.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Cook sugar and berries 10 minutes.
Mix flour, oil and milk. When berries are done, add margarine.
Drop dumplings into berries.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until dumplings are done.

title: ritz bits mix
directions: Grease a large cake pan or roaster.
Combine Ritz Bits and peanuts.
Pour mix into greased pan and set aside.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir.
Take from heat; add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over first mixture. Do not stir.
Bake at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and sliced apples in well greased pan.
Sprinkle with small amount of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, flour, quick oats and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine Hawaiian fruit punch, lemonade, orange juice, grape juice and water.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl (use an ice ring with orange slices and fresh mint leaves frozen in it if desired).
Resting bottle on rim of punch bowl, carefully pour in ginger ale.
Makes 30 to 35 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spoon into plate.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 package of pudding.
Add eggs, oil, nuts and soda.
Mix until blended and beat 4 minutes on medium.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool 20 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Cool and frost.

title: mud hens
directions: Make a dough of first 7 ingredients.
Spread dough on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Place chopped nuts over dough.
Beat egg white stiff; beat in brown sugar gradually.
Spread on top of nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scrambled egg muffins
directions: Brown sausage.
Beat eggs. Add onion, pepper, salt, pepper and garlic. Add cheese and sausage.
Spoon by 1/3 cup into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center comes out clean.

title: spring salad dressing
directions: Beat with egg beaters or whisk.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing together.
Spread mixture over each slice of rye bread.
Place cucumber slice on top of mixture. May top with pimento.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Can be a main meal.

title: cucumber salad(uborka salata)
directions: Remove seeds from cucumber halves by running spoon tip vertically top to bottom, scooping out seeds.
Slice out cucumbers thinly into half moon shaped slices.
Sprinkle with salt; put in bowl and cover with ice cubes.
Store cucumbers in refrigerator overnight.
Drain cucumber slices; shake off or squeeze out excess water.
Mix all dressing ingredients together.
Add cucumbers; let stand for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Combine everything, except hot dogs. Simmer until thickened. Grind hot dogs and add to sauce; stir. Cook for 15 minutes more. Serve with hot dogs on a bun.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook limas in margarine.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and cover with shredded American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: salmon and rice casserole
directions: Combine cheese, milk, salt and pepper in double boiler.
Heat until well blended and smooth.
Put a layer of cooked rice in well greased casserole.
On top arrange layers of salmon, olives and the cheese sauce.
Repeat ending with the cheese sauce.
Arrange slices of stuffed olives around edge for garnish.
Bake 60 minutes in 350°oven.

title: jessie cake
directions: Several hours before you make the cake, drain the cherries and cut them in two and rinse.
Leave in colander.

title: louise's barbecued chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and leave covered with fitted lid while preparing sauce.
Saute the onion in the cooking oil until tender.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, lemon juice, catsup, mustard, water, salt and red pepper to the sauteed onion and simmer ingredients for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from water, drain and pat dry.
Place in casserole dish and pour barbecue sauce on top.
Bake in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix the cream cheese with oleo.
Add sugar, flour and pecans. Batter will be thick and hard to mix.
Drop by small teaspoonful and bake only until very lightly browned at 350°.
Caution:
Do not overbake.
Different, but very good!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese, almonds and noodles.
Place in greased casserole dish, fairly shallow.
Cover with noodles, then cheese, then almonds.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut crunch slaw
directions: Toss cabbage and celery together.
Chill.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, salt, onion green pepper and cucumber.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss chilled vegetables with dressing.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top.
Serve.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons white vinegar and cane sugar with 1 quart of water.

title: toasted mushroom rounds
directions: Finely chop mushrooms. Saute 5 minutes in butter.
Blend in flour and salt. Stir in cream.
Cook until thick.
Add chives and lemon juice.

title: squash salad
directions: Slice squash into 1 1/2 quarts cold water into which the salt has been added.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and pimiento to squash.
Boil sugar, vinegar and mustard seed.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate covered overnight.

title: carrots for a crowd
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until crispy. Rinse in cold water; drain. Add onions and green peppers. In a small pan, mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil; stir. Pour over carrots, peppers and onions.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve hot as a vegetable or cold as a salad.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix cake mix, boiling water, eggs, pudding and oil until mixture is smooth and creamy, about 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar and water.
Boil until mixture reaches 300°.
Cool and stir in Kool-Aid.
Put apples on popsicle sticks and dip quickly into mixture.
Place coated apples onto a wax paper-lined cookie sheet to cool and dry.

title: danish puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 Tbsp. water over mixture.
Mix round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into 12 x 3 inch strips.

title: applesauce
directions: Quarter apples and put in large pan (size depends on amount of apples). Fill about halfway with water.
Put on stove and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until apples are soft.
Remove from heat and cool enough to handle.
Put through food strainer.
Add sugar or honey to taste.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Freezes well.

title: esther's heavenly cow
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt and pepper.
Add canned corn, noodles, tomatoes or tomato soup and water.
Cover with grated cheese.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Remove 2/3 cup of cake mix and set aside.
Mix remaining cake mix with egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini-mushroom cheese melt
directions: Brown mushrooms in liquid Butter Buds in a nonstick pan.
Stir in all the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheese on top and stir into mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 4.
Per serving:
Fat - 0.2 g, cholesterol - 1.6 mg, sodium - 69 mg, calories - 73.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Put cream cheese and cherry juice together; add pineapple and chopped cherries.
Add marshmallows, then fold in whipped cream. I like to add a little almond flavoring and a few drops of red food coloring to add more color.
Chill in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.

title: pineapple, cherry, raisin sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and sugar as for a pie crust.
Then beat eggs, vanilla and milk; mix together with flour mixture.
Roll larger part of dough and line jelly roll pan.
Pour the 3 cans of filling in separate sections.
Roll remaining dough and cut in strips for top layer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: In a large saucepan, heat all ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, tossing occasionally until cabbage is crisp-tender (about 5 minutes).

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter; stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire.
Pour mixture in roasting pan.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: david's deer stew
directions: Marinate deer meat in teriyaki sauce.
Roast deer meat until tender.
Chop into 1-inch pieces.
Place all ingredients in a large saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and reduce heat and cover pan.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover each breast with Swiss cheese.
Mix 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of wine.
Mix well and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover chicken with 2 cups Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix (not cubes).
Melt 1/3 cup butter or margarine, and drizzle over all.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: giant tostada
directions: Clean and peel onion, beets and carrot.
Place water and soup bone in large soup pot and bring to boil.
Add onion (whole), beets, carrot and potatoes; cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove beets and carrots; let cool.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in double boiler. Cook until thick. Add food coloring and let cool. Add berries and pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. Fold in with rest of ingredients. Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: pasta with shrimp
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions until al dente, tender but somewhat firm to the bite.
Drain and set aside. Meanwhile, cook chard or kale, using just the rinse water clinging to the leaves, in large skillet, covered, for 1 minute or just until wilted.
Drain and set aside.
Dry skillet.
Heat oil in same skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion; saute 1 minute. Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, wine, salt, black pepper and pepper flakes.
Simmer, stirring often, for 5 minutes, or until tomatoes are softened.
Stir greens and lemon juice into skillet.
Gently stir in shrimp.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over pasta.
Makes 6 servings.

title: winter squash muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine squash, apple, brown sugar, oil, egg and lemon peel.
(If squash and apple are freshly cooked, let them cool before adding egg.)
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Fold into squash mixture.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pig in the blanket
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place a sausage into each piece and pinch dough together at middle.
Cook until brown in a 350° oven.

title: main course vegetable salad
directions: *Amount depends on number of servings.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add peas, pimento, water chestnuts and mushroom soup, diluted with 1/4 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: john ben ghetty
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add noodles to meat; add vegetables, undrained, to meat and noodles.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve like this, or sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: meat loaf topping
directions: Mix all together and coat meat loaf.

title: life's recipe
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not choose too young.
When selected, give your choice thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Makes one quart. Really good with pork.

title: sponge cookies
directions: Beat all together in a bowl.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Before baking, sprinkle tops of cookie with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.
When cool, store in pot or Tupperware with layers of wax paper in between.
Before serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mini pizza
directions: Mash the canned biscuits flat into a circle.
Top with enough sauce to cover (about 1 tablespoon).
Top with cheese and a slice of pepperoni.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Any desired toppings can be used.
One can of sauce will cover about 30 biscuits.
Refrigerate or freeze leftover sauce for later use.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Then add rest of the ingredients and chill in refrigerator.
This recipe may be enlarged by using 2 of each ingredient, except strawberry jello and nuts.
Use only 1 each of them.
This is an excellent holiday salad.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion and salt and stir well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Shape into log and roll in nuts.
Chill several hours.

title: sugar cream pie squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
It will not look done, but is.
Do not overbake.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours in a 350° preheated oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add beans and taco seasoning.
Cut up lettuce and add tomatoes, onions and shredded cheese (quantity as desired).
Just before serving, mix warm meat mixture with salad mixture and add corn chips and dressing.
Serve warm.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: cream cheese christmas tree
directions: Blend cheeses.
Stir in garlic salt, green pepper and pimento. Place mixture on sheet of aluminum foil and flatten to 3/4-inch thickness in the shape of a Christmas tree.
I shape it like a solid sided triangle with a stump on the bottom.
Move the tree on foil to serving platter and trim away foil even with the tree shape.
Arrange pecan halves in rows across the tree until the entire surface is covered.
Refrigerate.
At serving time, arrange parsley or endive around the edge of tree and serve with crackers.

title: rob's baked chicken
directions: Prepare dough for Butter Pastry.
Spread dough-lined pan with mustard.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to firm dough.
Place shredded zucchini in a colander.
Salt lightly.
Let stand 15 minutes. Salt draws out bitter juices from zucchini.
Squeeze out moisture. Zucchini should be quite dry.
Preheat oven to 425° (220°C).
In a medium bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Mix in cream, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper, nutmeg and red pepper.
Add zucchini, cheese and half the nuts.
Pour zucchini mixture into chilled dough-lined pan.
Sprinkle remaining nuts over filling.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° (175°C).
