Continue baking 20 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sure to please pork chops
directions: Melt butter and saute onions. Combine all other ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes. Bake pork chops until almost done. Add sauce to pork chops for the remaining 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples. Sprinkle with sugar to taste.
If apples are flat, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Place in buttered 8-inch baking dish. Mix oatmeal, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Work butter into dry mixture.
Sprinkle over apples and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let dough rise in a greased bread pan until double.
Punch down and roll out.
Beat yolks lightly.
Add oil, Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic powder.
Beat thoroughly and brush on rolled out bread dough.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Pinch ends firmly together.
Place seam side down on pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with spaghetti sauce to dip.

title: wicked easy beef brisket
directions: Mix ingredients in a measuring cup and pour over meat in a shallow baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 4 - 5 hours at 300F.
Remove meat and reserve sauce.
Slice meat against the grain and serve with sauce.

title: perfect french toast
directions: Cut the bread diagonally to make 6 triangles.
In a bowl, beat the eggs until light and frothy.
Add the cream, salt, nutmeg and flavorings.
Soak the bread, a piece at a time, so that they absorb the egg-cream mixture thoroughly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch pie plate; set aside. Combine crumbs and oleo, mixing; press crumb mix over back and sides of plate.
Bake until crisp about 10 minutes, let cool.

title: baked boneless chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Spread very thin layer of this mixture on bottom of pan.
Cover bottom of baking pan with slices of chipped beef.
Add another thin layer of sauce. Place 2 to 3 strips of bacon on counter.
Place chicken breast on top of bacon and roll them up together.
Place two toothpicks through bacon and chicken breast to hold them together.
Place them in pan and cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour or until done.
Cook desired amount of Minute rice to go along with sauce and chicken.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Place in Pam sprayed baking dish. Trim edges off bread and cut in strips.
Layer bread strips both ways over peaches.
Melt margarine, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and egg.
Beat well; drip over bread strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles in a large amount of salted water and drain. Brown the hamburger.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and black pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: spanish corn
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon patties
directions: Put salmon into bowl. Add celery, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Now, add enough milk, a small amount at a time, until it sticks together to form a patty.
(Alternate more bread crumbs or milk until it sticks together good.)
Now, fry in oil.
Fry slowly until brown, then turn and brown the other side. Serve.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: queenie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions; drain well and dump into a big bowl.
Add grated cheese, reserving 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in margarine and eggs; no need to beat first. Just stir well to distribute evenly.
Add milk.
Mixture will be fairly liquid.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until set.
Serves 8.

title: surprise-filled cookies(yield: 4 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In bowl combine flour and baking powder; set aside.
In medium bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat on medium until smooth.
Add flour mixture; combine.
Dough will be firm.
Make 1 inch diameter balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Scoop out middle of dough ball. Do not scoop all the way through the cookie.
Place 1/2 teaspoon jam in the center of each dough ball.
Bake 22 to 24 minutes. Transfer to a cool flat surface.

title: fruit and orange fluff
directions: To prepare dressing, slowly beat pudding mix and milk in mixing bowl with rotary beater until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently beat in sour cream.
Fold in orange peel and juice.
Chill.

title: strawberry-fig preserves
directions: Wash plums and cut from seeds.
Measure after cut, then use 1 cup sugar for each 2 cups plums.
Combine sugar and plums in large saucepan.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring often.
(Probably will have to cook at least 45 minutes.)
When thick enough, put into hot jars and seal.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Spread cookie dough in 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake, using package directions or almost golden brown.
Do not overcook. Arrange candy over baked layer.
Bake until candy is softened. Spread evenly over baked layer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: granny's potato soup
directions: Peel the potatoes and grate on large grater.
Grate the carrot on medium sized grater.
Mince the celery.
Cut the onion fine. Put all of the vegetables into a saucepan and cover with water. Cook until tender.
Fry the bacon, break up and add to the vegetables. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stained-glass dessert
directions: Bring pineapple juice and 1/4 c. sugar to boil. Add in cold water and lemon jello mix. Set to cool. Mix lemon mixture in with Dream Whip. Blend 1/2 of Dream Whip-lemon mixture with jello squares and put on crust. Put remaining mixture on top.

title: mama hutch's oatmeal crisp cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Make dough into rolls 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil or plastic.
Chill thoroughly. Slice cookies about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: munching peanut brittle(microwave recipe)
directions: Stir sugar and syrup in microwave bowl and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes more until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour into lightly greased cookie sheet and cool for 30 minutes.
Then break and enjoy.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Place cupcake papers in small muffin tins.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom and fill 2/3 full with mix of remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool in tin.
Top with 1 tablespoon of either blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: chicken and black bean burritos
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Pour off all but 2 Tbsp fat or if omitting bacon, use 2 Tbls oil. Cook and stir raw chicken until chicken is not pink.
If using cooked chicken, skip this step and add to oil in skillet the garlic, chicken, beans, corn, red pepper, cumin, salt, cilantro and 1/2 cup of the Picante Sauce.
Simmer until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green onions and bacon bits.
Spoon a heaping 1/4 cup down center of tortilla, top with 1 Tbsp cheese. Roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spoon remaining 1 cup Picante Sauce over the tops and bake at 350 for 15 min.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash lettuce; pat dry and tear up into bite size pieces. Place in a salad bowl.
Break bacon into 1-inch pieces and add to lettuce.
Heat together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the lettuce,
tossing as you pour.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour	good.
Add
egg yellows, canned milk, water
and homogenized milk.
Mix all ingredients good; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a bubble. Remove
from
stove and add vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Stir
good and
pour	into cooked pie shell.	Use 3 egg whites (beaten until
they
hold
a
peek)
with sugar added. Place on
top
of pie
and return to oven.
Cook until golden brown.	You may want to add a little coconut on the top before browning.

title: homestyle macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta according to pkg. directions.
Transfer to colander and rinse under cold water; drain.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Add cooled pasta and toss to coat.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook broccoli in small amount of salted water, about 5 minutes, just until tender.
Drain well.
Mix broccoli, onion, peppers and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over vegetables.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend in processor the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well until smooth.
Pour mixture into 9-inch graham crust.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with a dab of Cool Whip and a few crushed peanuts on each slice.
Make slices small; very rich.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: coconut shrimp with pineapple salsa
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, devein and rinse shrimp in cold water. Drain on paper towels until dry.

title: white chili
directions: Chop chicken in bite size cubes.
In a large skillet, pour chicken broth
and add white beans with liquid.
Simmer.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add jalapeno peppers with liquid, then add to chicken broth with chicken and stir in cumin, oregano, cayenne and hot sauce.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve with your favorite corn bread.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Beat eggs with milk, mayonnaise and flour in a medium bowl. Stir in cheese and bacon.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugars in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and corn flakes and stir well.
Press into a shallow pan (like a cookie sheet) that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with canned chocolate frosting.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup oats, butter, boiling water, honey and salt.
Cool to warm (105° to 115°).
Stir in yeast.
Add 2 eggs and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes). (Add more flour as needed until dough no longer sticks.)
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.

title: party spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup of the butter.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and 2/3 cup of the Parmesan; stir in spinach, mushrooms and artichokes.

title: a doggy treat!!!(dog biscuits)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in beef (or chicken) broth, Gravy Master, milk and eggs.
Knead mixture until dough forms, then roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares, or use your favorite cookie shape.
Place pieces on a cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave biscuits in oven for 8 hours.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Mix and press graham crackers and butter in lightly greased pan.
Layer next four ingredients on top of graham crackers.
Pour can of condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parsonage punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, honey and cherry juice.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Spoon in vanilla ice cream.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Stir gently.
Serve at once.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir milk, flour and butter in pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture boils, add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked macaroni in a greased pan. Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Wash and separate fillets; place in a casserole.
Mix butter, lime juice and spices; pour over fillets.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip orange pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cut butter and cream cheese into 1-inch slices; place in bowl of food processor.
Add sugar and process until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Add eggs, vanilla and orange peel; process until blended. Add flour and baking powder; process until blended.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan to wire racks.
Cool completely; sprinkle confectioners sugar over cake.

title: peanut butter round-up cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and peanut butter, then flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats.
Shape to form balls, about 1 inch in size.
Place on ungreased sheet; press with fork to make crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: green chile and chicken stew
directions: In a large stockpot, combine chicken, water, oregano, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Boil for 10 minutes and then simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and let cool until you are able to take meat off bones.
Discard skin and bones.
Return chicken meat to pot.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic, and green chiles.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook another 10 minutes.
For a shortcut you may use chicken broth and frozen cut-up chicken instead of cooking the chicken, but it is not as good as making it from scratch!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with olive oil. Slice tomatoes and place on bottom of casserole. Slice zucchini and layer on top of the tomatoes. Slice onion and cover zucchini.
Sprinkle a mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan and repeat layering process. Cover second tier with tomatoes and sprinkle with olive oil, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crusty apple cobbler
directions: What To Do:
Place apples and 1/4 cup brown sugar in greased casserole. Mix well.
In medium bowl, mix butter or margarine and remaining brown sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs and milk. Mix well.

title: asparagus hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut the crusts off bread and flatten with a rolling pin.
Roll one spear of asparagus in each slice of flattened bread.
Dip rolled bread in margarine and roll in cheese.
(They can be frozen until ready to use.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then broil for 1 minute.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients, then fold in fruit. Refrigerate.

title: poppy seed noodles 'n cream
directions: In 3-quart saucepan cook noodles; drain well.
Return to pan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and heated through, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: In wok or large frying pan heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Warm on medium-high heat.
Add meat, stirring quickly.
Add vegetables (desired amounts) and stir quickly and consistently. Add oyster sauce to taste.
(Oyster sauce has a high sodium content so be careful not to use too much.)
Stir-fry is ready when vegetables are pliable but still crisp.

title: italian square zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with spoon.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and scrub mushrooms.
Remove all stems from 12 large fresh mushrooms and chop very fine.
Place stems in skillet with melted butter and saute slightly.
Add finely chopped parsley, breadcrumbs and/or ham or any of the other suggestions listed.
Spoon into each of the mushrooms and bake in oven (350° for about 10 minutes, or until lightly browned).
Serve as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: orange pecans
directions: Boil together to soft ball (cook until you can pick up the drop).
Add small lump of butter (about a teaspoon).
Add 3 cups pecan halves and stir until well covered and the coating starts to look creamy.
Spread out on waxed paper.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cream the sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add flour, baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Make a heavy paste of the cocoa and boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add and blend well.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine. Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Mix until light and fluffy. Spoon into crusts.
Whip cream until stiff. Fold in pineapple and nuts. Spoon on top of sugar mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Make a hole in dry mixture and combine.
Add blueberries.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in muffin tins with paper liners.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise.
Add milk and bake in muffin tins at 350 degrees until brown.

title: touchdown tacos
directions: Cook meat in large skillet over medium-high heat until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain fat from pan.
Add rice, taco seasoning and green onions.
Stir until well blended and thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes.
Fill taco shells with the rice and beef mixture.
Top each taco with lettuce, cheese and salsa.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the brown sugar, white sugar, margarine, vanilla and peanut butter. Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.

title: almond-green pepper loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 1 1/2-quart oiled casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Uncover last 10 minutes to brown on top.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Bake 20 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers and butter.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Put the oleo in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Turn oven to 350° and put pan in oven.
Mix in a bowl the flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk.
Pour over melted oleo. Spread blueberries over mixture. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over the berries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together baking powder, flour and salt; stir in first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Form dough into 1/2-inch balls and place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down slightly with fork.
Bake at 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix ingredients and form into ball.
Chill.
Coat with topping.

title: mandelbrot
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the margarine and the sugar. Beat in the eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine the flours and the baking powder.
Add to the wet ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in the almonds.
Form the dough into a long loaf about 1-inch high and 4-inches wide.
Place on the ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° until browned on the bottom, about 25 minutes.
Remove the bread from the oven; place it on a cutting board and cut it into 26 (1/2-inch thick) slices.
Arrange the slices on the baking sheet and bake until toasted on one side. Turn them over and toast the other side.
Cool on a wire rack. Yield:
Approximately 26 (3 x 1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to boil sugar, white vinegar, celery seed and salt. Pour over pickles, onion and pepper.
Keep in refrigerator one day before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk for about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese to pudding and beat until smooth.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Put a layer of pudding mixture in pie crust, and then a layer of chopped strawberries.
Put the remainder of pudding on top of strawberries.
Chill for one hour.
This recipe may be used with different kinds of fruits.

title: yummy s'mores
directions: Place graham cracker square on a paper towel; top with chocolate bar and marshmallow.
Microwave for 15 to 20 seconds on High until marshmallow puffs.
Top with graham cracker square; allow to stand 1 minute, until chocolate melts.
You'll definitely want some more!
Makes 1 serving.

title: diabetic banana date cookies
directions: Mix bananas, dates and oil.
Add oatmeal, nuts, salt and vanilla; let stand 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: savory apple roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Line roasting pan with aluminum foil. Core and cut apples into quarters. Cut sweet potatoes into 6 to 8 large pieces. Cut onions into small wedges. Combine apples, vegetables, olive oil and garlic. Roast in prepared pan 40 to 45 minutes or until sweet potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with balsamic vinegar before serving. Serve hot or cold. Makes 6 servings.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pudding, milk, chips and butter in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat, cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip and grated chocolate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to make corn bread and set aside. Saute hamburger and set aside.
Grate Cheddar cheese and set aside.
Oil a 9 x13-inch baking dish.
Pour in half of corn bread mixture.
Sprinkle with meat, then cheese, onion and finally jalapenos.
Pour on remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares to serve.

title: kid's spaghetti(kids love this!)
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter.
In a separate Dutch oven, combine soup, sauce, paste and catsup. Add onions and pepper to sauce and begin cooking.
In skillet over medium heat, cook hamburger and chili powder until brown. Drain.
Add to sauce. Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles, drain and top with sauce.

title: grandma's butterscotch pie
directions: Use a heavy pan and cook first 3 ingredients until very thick, like molasses.

title: shrimp loaf
directions: Slice French bread and hollow out both top and bottom halves. Toast bread removed from center and inside of both halves in broiler.
Make bread crumbs out of bread removed from center of loaf, using a food processor; set bread aside.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, margarine and pineapple.
Add bread (cut up in small squares).
Put all in a well buttered baking dish. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Great with ham.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix your 2 cheeses.

title: can't fail pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in a pie plate and mix with a fork.
When thoroughly blended, spread mixture on bottom and sides of pan, leaving enough at upper edge to flute.
Prick many times bottom and sides with fork and bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Set aside. Combine soup, milk, chopped onion, pimiento, green pepper and black pepper.
Place over low heat.
Add cubed cheese and stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni and tuna in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend in cheese sauce.
Bake in 325° oven about 20 minutes.
Can top with crushed potato chips before baking.

title: potatoes and sausage
directions: Place sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
When potatoes feel tender, add sausage and cook until heated thoroughly.

title: party snack
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all snacks.
Mix popping oil with Ranch dressing.
Coat snacks.
Stir every 1/2 hour for 4 hours.
Makes 25 cups.

title: chocolate chip (m&m) cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar and shortening in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips or M&M's.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 12 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: tammy's fruit salad
directions: *Peaches, strawberries, bananas, pineapple, grapes, apples, blueberries, orange or any fruit of your choice can be used.

title: lynn's casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion while noodles cook.
Combine meat, noodles, chili sauce, cheese, soup, green pepper, salt and water; mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with slices of margarine and cheese.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until creamy.
Pour all ingredients into electric or hand cranked freezer.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: tortilla appetizer wedges
directions: In medium bowl combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well. Stir in chilies, onions and jalapenos.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 tortilla with about 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture; top with another tortilla.
Continue spreading and stacking tortillas until stack is 4 tortillas high; top with another tortilla that has not been spread with cream cheese mixture.
Make another stack with remaining 5 tortillas.
Wrap tortilla stacks in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut each stack into 18 wedges.
Arrange pinwheel fashion around cup of salsa, picante sauce or salsa verde.
Makes 38 appetizer servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at
300° for one hour.
Let cool before cutting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, eggs, half of crumbs,
half of cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in 1 quart
baking
dish.
Sprinkle
with remaining crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato and cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, then drain.
Melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and sliced carrot.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Add flour to butter, stir until smooth.
Add milk and bouillon cubes, stir until mixed.
Add in potatoes and when thickened, add the cheese.
Stir until dissolved.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, orange rind, sugar, pineapple and celery together well.
Mix jello, boiling water and cold water together. Allow jello mixture to jell slightly.
Then add cranberry mixture. Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine the 3 bananas, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add the butter.
Stir in the flour and baking soda until creamy.
Stir in the butter and buttermilk.
Bake in a baking pan at 350° for 30 minutes, then reduce the heat to 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: quick snacks
directions: Break grahams in half. Frost with generous portion of frosting.
Place second half on top and chill.
Serve cold with milk.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until browned. Drain on paper towel.
Discard pan drippings.
Add next 8 ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and thyme.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together.
To prepare beverage, mix 2 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.
Store mix in airtight container.

title: hamburg noodle casserole
directions: Saute hamburg with pepper and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add onion rings and bake 5 minutes more (onion rings may be omitted).

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up the sides.
Seal perforations.
Bake for 14 to 19 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool completely.
Blend sour cream with the dressing mix; spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer size pieces.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Mix chicken, onions, peppers, soup and Tabasco.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6.

title: zesty salsa supreme!
directions: In small bowl, combine cucumber, pepper, carrot, taco sauce, green chiles and parsley until well blended.
Spoon a rounded teaspoonful vegetable mixture onto each Wheat 'n Bran Triscuits wafer.
Top with a dollop of guacamole and garnish with carrot, if desired.

title: pocket of pizza sandwiches
directions: In a large skillet, brown turkey and onion; drain.
Stir in pepperoni, Italian seasoning and pizza sauce.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; stir in half of the cheese.
Line each pocket bread half with lettuce leaf.
Fill each with 1/6 of turkey mixture.
Top each with 1/6 of remaining cheese. If desired, serve with additional pizza sauce.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: jello-cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and add to cherry Jell-O.
Add boiling water.
After cool, add other ingredients.
Stir often to keep mixture even.
Once it starts to set, it should not have to be stirred.

title: low-fat artichoke parmesan spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Gently fold in artichokes.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole coated with vegetable cooking spray. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serve with assorted raw vegetables or low-fat crackers.
Yields 3 1/4 cups.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and slice potatoes as large French fries.
Place in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; sprinkle over potatoes. Mix water and juice and pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter, cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sweet and sour chicken with oriental fried rice
directions: Coat chicken with sweet and sour sauce that has bee brought just to a boil.
Prepare rice.
Fry in electric skillet or frying pan the vegetable oil or melted margarine and cooked rice.
Add soy sauce and heat through.
Spread sweet and sour chicken over a bed of the prepared rice and serve.

title: stuckey spoon bread
directions: Mix milk and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add meal, salt and sugar and stir until thick. Set aside and let cool, then add the egg yolks.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the other mixture.
Pour into a baking dish and bake about 45 to 50 minutes, until browned, at 375°.
Serve immediately.

title: cream-style chicken casserole
directions: Rinse
or wash chicken thoroughly. Season to taste with seasoned salt
and	black
pepper.	Place
in
350° oven until brown.
Add
1 can of mushrooms, 2 cans of water, celery, bell pepper and	onion.	Return	to
oven
and resume baking for 20 minutes or	until
gravy thickens.	Remove from oven and serve over bed of rice or white mashed potatoes.

title: artichoke parmesan cheese spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Gently stir in artichokes.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: "4-step" chocolate dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into an oblong pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1/2 cream cheese, 1/2 container whipped topping and powdered sugar over cooled base.
Combine puddings and mix until thickened; spread on second layer.
Spread on the remaining whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts or chocolate shavings.
Refrigerate overnight.
May be frozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Put into buttered 9-inch square pan; chill.
Nuts can be added, if desired.

title: pasta and cheese toss
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In large skillet, brown ham in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add cream, egg yolk, cheeses and paprika.
Blend until smooth.
Toss pasta and pimentos with sauce over medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Brown hamburger; add soup, both sauces and milk.
Put a layer of Doritos, then a layer of meat mixture, Doritos and meat.
Crush some Doritos on top and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chinese peas and shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Heat oil; add shrimp and cook quickly until pink, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add pea pods, onions, ginger and garlic; toss ingredients.
Cook on high for 1 minute.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, water and soy sauce.
Pour over shrimp mixture and cook until thick, about 1 minute.

title: cinnamon sweet potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in pan with butter flavoring.
Add brown sugar, powdered cinnamon and 1/4 cup syrup drained from sweet potatoes. Simmer for a few minutes, then add drained sweet potatoes.
Cook over low heat, stirring often to coat potatoes with a glaze.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick coating.
In bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat margarine until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in egg substitute and dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla, apples, applesauce and nuts.

title: biscuits
directions: Carefully stir water into mix to form a stiff dough that can be removed from mixing bowl in a single lump.
Place dough on lightly floured surface and knead briefly, using extra flour to keep dough from sticking to fingers or board. Pat or roll
dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass dipped in flour.
Place biscuits on pans, bake at 425° until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Prick holes in pie shell with fork and bake pie shell at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces about the size of a quarter.
Break cheese into bite size pieces.
Arrange shrimp, bread, and cheese in several layers in greased
casserole.
Pour margarine or butter over this mixture.	Beat eggs.
Add mustard and salt to eggs; then add milk.
Mix together and pour this over ingredients in casserole.	Let stand a minimum of 3 hours, preferably overnight, in refrigerator, covered.
Bake one hour in 350° oven, covered.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, butter and water and let set for 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together by hands.
When well mixed, add nuts.
Mold into long roll, size of crackers, and chill.
Slice and bake at 350° until crisp.
Can be stored in refrigerator and baked as needed.

title: company's coming ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease dish real good.
Arrange ham slices in dish.
Stir remaining ingredients with mixing spoon in mixing bowl.
Spread over ham.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes until ham is heated through and preserves bubble.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday cider
directions: Mix cider, orange juice and lemonade according to directions. Add brown sugar.
Tie cinnamon sticks together.
Add cloves and allspice. Bring to a boil. Let simmer about 10 minutes. May be served with sliced apples in a cup, mandarin oranges or cherry. Or just pour out of the barrel thermo hot.

title: apple pie with cranberry
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. In a large bowl, combine apples, orange juice and cranberries. Stir together sugar, flour and spices; stir this mixture into apples. Spoon into pastry crust and dab butter over apples. Put second crust over apple mixture. Cut slits in the top and seal edges. Cover edges of crust with foil. Bake for 25 minutes. Remove foil and bake 25 to 30 more minutes, until crust is golden brown. Brush top with butter and sprinkle with sugar, if you like.

title: hashed brown omelet
directions: In a
or
inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Leave drippings
in skillet; drain bacon and crumble.
Mix the hash browns,
onion
and
green	pepper; put in skillet.
Cook over low heat until underside is crisp and brown.
Blend eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon
of
salt	and
dash of pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with
cheese
and bacon.
Cover; cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Loosen omelet.
Serve in wedges.

title: fruity cookie recipe
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and gelatin; cream well after each addition.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with gelatin.
Decorate as desired.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apple cream cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, orange juice and powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth, then stir in apples; chill.
Use this as a spread for banana bread or other fruit breads.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frypan.
Sprinkle rice over chops.
Cover with tomatoes and water; add seasoning.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, drained green beans and soup; mix well and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes while hot; add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon in mounds over meat mixture in casserole. Sprinkle with paprika, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Crumble ground beef and onion, microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until meat loses its pink color.
Drain.
Stir in soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly in a casserole dish.
Spread corn on top of meat mixture.
Spoon mounds of potatoes over corn.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes or until casserole is hot.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 2 to 3 1/2 minutes until cheese melts, rotating dish after half of cooking time.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Cooking time: 17 minutes.

title: fresh orange layer cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vegetable shortening, grated orange peel, 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix in mixer on slow to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape sides frequently.
Add remaining 1/3 cup liquid, eggs.
Continue beating 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with 7 Minute Frosting.
Sprinkle each frosted layer with grated rind and chopped pecans.

title: rigatoni and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rigatoni and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 24 hours. Prepare rigatoni as directed on package; drain.
Immediately toss with tomato mixture.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: pickle corn
directions: Corn should be extra
full.
Cook on cob; cut off.
Put in churn; pour salt
water and vinegar mixture over corn until covered completely.
Then
cover
corn
with clean cloth, then weight down with 2 heavy plates.
Let set for 2 weeks.

title: best ever banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Mix well for approximately 2 minutes.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Add half of cool whip and mix well.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding mix, end with pudding.
Top with remaining cool whip spreading evenly over top and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.

title: green bean and potato casserole
directions: Cook green beans.
Place bacon grease and onion in skillet. Saute until onions are slightly brown.
Put in with beans.
Add butter.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.
Add potatoes and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Place in baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Top with crisp bacon.
Serves 4.

title: honey syrup
directions: Combine in a saucepan the sugar and water. Boil and reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add honey and lemon juice, stirring well. Return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles; rinse and drain.
Brown beef and onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: parmesan rice
directions: Cook rice with bouillon cube as directed.
Stir in
cheese and bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: apple-walnut supreme cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Add dry ingredients alternately with apple mixture.
By hand, stir in walnuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: farm house sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, continuing to beat.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Roll on floured canvas, fairly thick.
Cut with large round cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with what you desire.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
These cookies should be large and soft.
Chill the dough before rolling.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix 1 container lemon yogurt and mix with half the Cool Whip. Put in pie crust.
Mix 1 container strawberry yogurt with 1 mashed banana and other half of Cool Whip.
Put on top of first layer of yogurt.
Place in freezer until frozen.
Let set out a few minutes before slicing.

title: cholesterol watchers cinnamon oat bran muffins
directions: Combine milk and bran.
Add egg, brown sugar, cinnamon and oil; mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to oat bran mixture until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until light golden brown at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal.
Toss with fork.
Add next five ingredients; beat with mixer until smooth and blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set and lightly brown on top.

title: pork steak casserole
directions: Cut pork steak into bite-size pieces and brown together with chopped bell pepper and sliced celery.
Add the vinegar and simmer 30 minutes.
Add Veg-All, tomato sauce, water and rice.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put 1 cup Pet milk, 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate morsels, 1 cup miniature marshmallows and 1/4 teaspoon salt into a heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens.

title: barbecups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Place one biscuit in each ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up side to the edge of the cup.
Spoon meat into cups. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef roast barbecue(six servings)
directions: Combine roast and chopped onion in a 4-quart crock-pot. Combine cola and next 7 ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup in refrigerator.
Pour remaining mixture over roast and onion.
Cover and cook on high 6 hours or until roast is very tender.
You can test with a fork to see if it shreds easily and cook a little longer if needed.
Drain and discard liquid.
Shred roast.	Keep warm.
Combine reserved 1/2 cup cola mixture, ketchup and butter in a small saucepan.
Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until thoroughly heated.
Pour over shredded roast, stirring gently.
Spoon onto buns.
Is good to add coleslaw on top of barbecue.
Serve with chips and pickle spears.

title: one-dish oven meal
directions: Put in casserole in order listed. Cover with cream of mushroom and milk. Bake in a covered dish at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Arrange salmon steaks (or whole salmon) in glass baking dish.
Pour marinade over salmon and cover for 3 hours or longer.
Turn several times.
Wrap in heavy foil and grill (medium to low) for 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Serve with mustard sauce:
1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup mustard and 2 teaspoons horseradish (or to taste).

title: marinated cornish hens
directions: Blend the preceding together. Marinate hens for 3 hours, turning occasionally. Bake, broil or grill hens as desired.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add carrots; mix well.
Add baking soda, flour and cinnamon; blend well. Grease one 9 x 12-inch pan or two 9-inch baking pans.
Add mix. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until fully cooked.

title: sunny carrots
directions: Bias-slice carrots crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots; toss to coat evenly.

title: turtles
directions: Cook sugar, 1 cup milk, corn syrup and butter vigorously. Gradually add the other cup of milk (keep it boiling), stirring constantly.
Test in cold water until soft balls form.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Cool enough to handle.
Create turtles by pressing pecan meats into four corners of a teaspoon of the candy (caramels).
Set on wax paper and let dry.
Dip into milk chocolate that has been heated in double boiler.
Lay turtles on wax paper to cool.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: elephant ears
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon together in a bowl.
Take each biscuit, roll flat and drop into hot grease in a saucepan for a few seconds.
Take out and dip into mixture.

title: sangria
directions: Mix all but club soda.
Chill.
To serve, mix in club soda.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Break Nickles Angel Food Cake in small pieces and put in 9x13 pan.
Pour jello over cake.
Be sure to soak jello into cake. Place strawberries (sliced) into cake.
Refrigerate until jelled, then spread cool whip over top of it.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.
"Enjoy".

title: great minestrone soup
directions: Brown everything in oil; break up tomatoes.
Simmer 40 to 60 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese when serving (if desired).
A large pot is needed for cooking.
Great for freezing.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup from hard brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat after boiling has ceased. Stir in flavoring and food coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet or powdered sugar on foil.
Pour the candy on powdered sugar.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Makes 2 pounds.

title: bertha's biscuits
directions: Cut like pie crust.
Add 2/3 cup milk.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Put beans on the bottom.
The 2nd layer is the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream with taco mix and layer over avocado.
Add lettuce, tomato and scallions.
Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Blend water and egg whites and beat stiff.
Mix sugar, salt and spices and add to mixture.
Dip pecans with mix.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for one hour.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into square greased cake pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: yuk fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Put in oblong pan and let set.

title: curried shrimp salad(serves 4)
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients from shrimp through pineapple chunks.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill until serving time.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Toss together all other ingredients while macaroni is cooking.
(Leave cheese until last.) Add macaroni to mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: feathery fudge cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 9-inch baking pans.
In a small saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and let cool.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Add dry ingredients and cold water alternately, beating after each addition, just until combined.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly.
Frost with Feathery Fudge Frosting.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Heat oil in pot. Add onion and garlic; saute lightly. Add fish, celery, potatoes, tomatoes, basil, bay leaves, salt, pepper and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer gently 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are just done. Add string beans, if desired, during last 10 minutes of cooking time. Remove bay leaves. Garnish with fresh parsley. Add additional water if necessary. Good left over, flavor improves. Makes 2 quarts. Serve with crusty hard rolls or dark bread.

title: german apple kuchen
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, coconut and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in butter (soft) with blender until consistency of oatmeal.
Stir in egg, milk and vanilla extract. Spread as dough in bottom of buttered 11-inch pie plate.
Toss apples, raisins, nuts, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together; then place evenly on top of batter in pie plate.
In a small bowl, cream together cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add lemon juice and egg yolks; beat until smooth.
Pour this topping evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or ice cream, if so desired.
Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: devil's food cake with chocolate fudge frosting
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 3/4 cups sugar, cocoa powder and baking soda.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until combined, about 30 seconds.
Then beat on medium to high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Thoroughly wash beaters.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into batter. Spray two 9-inch round pans with nonstick coating and dust with flour.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: medallion sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cream shortening; add sugar gradually creaming well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each. Add vanilla. Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.

Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Roll out very thin (less than 1/8 inch) on lightly floured surface. Cut with floured 3 inch cutter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake on ungreased sheets in hot oven (400°) for 5 to 8 minutes or until done.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: emerald isle salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Place pineapple juice in saucepan and add marshmallows.
Place on medium heat and heat until marshmallows melt.
Add mixture to jello mixture; chill until it starts to jell, then add pineapple chunks, cottage cheese and nuts.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.

title: saucy pork steaks
directions: Tenderize steaks by pounding with meat mallet.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place steaks on grill about 4 inches above low coals.
Cook about 20 minutes, turning and basting occasionally.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with steaks, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened and then cool.
Add fruit and nuts to thickened mixture and mix well.
Add Cool Whip to apple mixture.
Chill for 2 hours or more.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
In a skillet, cook onion, sausage and beef until meat is brown.
Combine meat mixture and spaghetti in pot.
Add corn, with the juice, and olives, without the juice. Mix in 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Whisk together flour, soda and salt.
Melt white chocolate in double boiler.
Add margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Put in rest of milk and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Dredge fruit in part of flour.
Add extracts to egg mixture.
After dredging fruit; add to egg mixture and also add remaining flour.
Add nuts and mix well. Grease tube pan.
Pour batter into tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
(Put a pan with 2 cups water on bottom shelf of oven.)
Batter can be baked in 1 pound loaf pans or cupcakes at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: forget-me cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat in vanilla and salt.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Place in preheated 350° oven turned off, overnight.

title: cheddar spoonbread
directions: Scald milk.
Slowly sprinkle cornmeal over milk, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring over low heat until mixture has thickened (5 to 10 minutes).
Add cheese, oleo, salt and sugar.
Stir until cheese and oleo are melted.
Stir in eggs; mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until firm.
Serve immediately.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with canned chocolate sour cream frosting.

title: grandma lyla's norwegian flat bread
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand until cool.
Add enough flour to roll out thin.
Dough may be formed into long roll, then cut into pieces large enough to make flat bread to fit the size of baking surface.
Bake on both sides (medium-ungreased) to a light brown in hot oven or on lefse plate or griddle.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients (adding apples last).
This dough will be stiff.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick stuck in dough comes out clean.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package of jello with 1 cup boiling water; stir in frozen 1/2 pint strawberries until dissolved.
Stir in 1 can crushed pineapple and juice and 2 diced bananas.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over firm mixture.
Repeat jello mixture and pour over sour cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chat 'n' chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan, well-greased.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cut into squares when slightly warm.

title: low sugar low-fat flank steak
directions: Place steak in an 11 x 2-inch glass dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Blue cheese together.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Marinate at least 3 or 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and dice the potatoes.
Put half in a 9 x 15-inch pan with 1/2 onion and 1/2 the cheese.
In another pan, melt margarine.
Add chicken soup.
Remove from burner and add 1/2 on potato, onion and cheese.
Then add more potatoes, rest of cheese and onion and soup.
Add sour cream. Put pieces of butter on top and sprinkle with cornflakes on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Stir salad dressing mix into mashed potatoes.
If desired, add butter or margarine.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper chops.
Brown in hot skillet with fat.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until chops are tender. M-M-M delicious.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients. Add beaten egg whites and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix the flour and pecans together.
Melt margarine and pour into flour and pecans.
Stir until well blended.
Press in the bottom of a large Pyrex baking dish. Bake at 350° until brown. Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; add garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain, then add Prego sauce and tomato juice.
Simmer for 10 minutes, after it boils once.
In a greased 9 x 13 pan, put 1/3 cup water, then a layer of uncooked lasagna noodles, then hamburger sauce and then cheese.

Do one more layer of each, ending with cheese on top. Make the lasagna the night before and let set in refrigerator overnight.	Bake at 350° for one hour and 10 minutes with the lid off to brown cheese.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together for 20 minutes Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add lemon extract.
Fold in 3/4 cup of 7-Up.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheddar supreme salsa dip
directions: Mix together salsa and cream cheese until it's very creamy. Then layer onions, then peppers, then tomatoes and top with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and pour over the mixture in oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for exactly 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and pecans.
(Note:
Pecans may be omitted if you desire.)

title: peach shake
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 95 calories.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into saucepan.	Stir constantly over medium-high
heat.	Let
cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Clean chicken, removing all possible fat and boil until tender.
Then set aside to cool.
Strain broth and put in refrigerator.
Fat will settle on top and you can skim it off later.
Prepare potatoes, onions, garlic and cook in water with oregano, salt, pepper and green chiles.
When mixture starts boiling add rice.
Cook 20 minutes.
Skin and debone and cut up the chicken.
Add it and cook another 10 minutes. Skim the grease off the broth and add to mixture.
Blend the tomatoes in a blender and add.
Heat mixture through.
Serve.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Cut steak into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Brown each side in shortening.
Place in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan. Simmer 3 minutes.
Pour over steak.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion.
Add enough water to cover all and cook until tender.
Add Carnation milk, butter, salt and cornstarch mixed with cold water to potato mixture and cook until the soup has a consistency of heavy cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice from crushed pineapple.
Add pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight before serving.

title: cajun-style seafood gumbo
directions: Start with equal amounts of flour and oil (1 cup) to make roux.
Heat oil on medium heat until hot; add flour, stirring constantly until brown.
Remove from heat and pour into large pot. Add tomatoes and 1 can water; simmer over medium-low heat and stir.
Boil crabs on separate burner until cooked.
Set aside.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Combine dill, buttermilk, mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Stir to coat.
Serve immediately or chill for later.

title: date balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook 2 minutes on medium heat. Add remaining ingredients to other mixture, stir and form into balls.

title: popcorn or apple dip
directions: In a small bowl combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir well.
Dip!

title: milwaukee-style standing rib roast
directions: If frozen, completely thaw roast in refrigerator.
Plan to roast meat in the morning.
Allow several hours to elapse between Step 1 and Step 2.
tags: standing rib or rolled beef roast

title: basic roll mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients well and store in plastic container.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, onions and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In saucepan, dissolve cornstarch and salt in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla. Cool slightly. Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain. Arrange bananas on bottom of pie shell. Pour filling over bananas; cover. Chill 4 hours. Spread whipped cream on top. Slice last banana and dip in lemon juice and drain. Layer banana on top of whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, Karo and 1 can of milk.
Boil slowly and steadily.
Add second can of milk (add slowly).
Stir constantly. Cook 1 hour or until it forms a firm ball in water.
Stir in chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour in flat pan or on platter greased with oleo.
When cold, cut and wrap.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add green beans, tomato sauce, onion and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add noodles to boiling water and cook until tender.
Add all ingredients together and cook to heat.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, margarine and vanilla well. Stir in pecans, coconut and chocolate chips. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: homos min sahul
directions: Fry onion until golden brown.
Add potatoes, tomato paste and about 3 cans (from paste) of water.
Cook until potatoes are done. You may add more water if needed.
Season to taste.
Add chickpeas just before potatoes are done.
This is a great Lenten dish.

title: golden cereal nut clusters(makes about 2 dozen)
directions: Chop candy coating into small pieces. Place in heavy 10-inch skillet. Cover and heat over low heat about 5 minutes or until coating is soft. Remove from heat. Stir until smooth and creamy. Stir in cereal until well coated. Stir in peanuts and marshmallows. Drop mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper or aluminum foil. Sprinkle with candy sprinkles. Let stand 1 to 2 hours or until completely set. When ready to serve, place into cupcake liners.

title: pineapple coconut inside-out cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix, 1 package of the pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl with mixer on low speed 1 minute or until blended.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups of the coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans. Cool completely on wire racks.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add rest of water, sugar, oil and salt.
Add flour slowly after well mixed.
Beat egg white and blend into mixture.
Cover bowl.
Let rise until double. Place on floured surface.
Knead back to original size.
Cut in pieces about golf ball size.
Form ball; place in greased pan. Grease top of rolls.
Let rise again until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Lightly wipe top of rolls with margarine. Serve.

title: orange whip
directions: Put in a blender; add ice to fill line.
Blend.

title: quick clam chowder
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a quick boil. Simmer with lid on until potatoes are tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given with mixer until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: carotte blanchie(white carrot)
directions: White Carrots:
Use the same Bechamel Sauce in Onion Pie recipe.
Substitute Parmesan cheese in place of Swiss cheese. Prepare sauce the same way.
Boil carrots, but do not cook thoroughly.
Drain carrots.
Place drained carrots in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange fall fruit combo
directions: Combine fruits and Curacao in bowl; chill.
Whip heavy cream with confectioners sugar.
Stir in orange peel and cinnamon. Serve over fruit.

title: brian's candy bars
directions: Heat the chocolate in the microwave for 1 minute; stir. Repeat until the chocolate is melted and smooth, 3 to 4 minutes total.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.

title: mini beef loaves
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, milk, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Press half of the beef mixture in bottoms and halfway up sides of 12 ungreased 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups.
Fill each with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Top with remaining beef mixture, pressing edges to seal.
Place muffin pan in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until done, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef or turkey and drain.
Combine dirty rice mix, meat and 2 1/2 to 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add additional rice.
Reduce heat, stir, cover and simmer over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dump salad or dessert
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer bread slices to completely cover bottom of pan.
Layer meat, cheese and sprinkle parsley.
Cover completely with another layer of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread and meat layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Crush cornflakes and spread over top of casserole.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, eggs and egg whites; beat until blended and smooth.
Mix in sugar, all spices and salt, blending well.
Stir in crumbs.
Spray high sided 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour pie filling into pie plate. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool pie on wire rack; refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Cut in wedges; serve with dollop of whipped cream.
Do not forget to spray pie plate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake or make fork indentions and pour icing over cake, just out of the oven.

title: cake mix bars
directions: Mix until moist.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Make 4 or 5 thin layers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: simply delicious cookies
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and flour.
Roll into 24 balls and form in small muffin tins or paper and fill with jam, etc. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, vanilla and egg in large bowl.

Stir in flour. Press evenly into bottom of ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2). Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until brown. Cool 20 minutes. Heat corn syrup, 2 tablespoons butter and butterscotch chips in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chips melt. Remove from heat. Cool 10 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and sausage
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni and add tomato soup.
Add water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Arrange sausage on top.
Bake in a greased casserole dish until sausage is brown, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Strain juice through nylon to make 4 cups. Place juice in large saucepan. Add strained lemon juice and sugar. Mix well. Place on high heat, stirring constantly. Stir in pectin and bring to a rolling boil. Boil 1 minute and 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Skim off foam. Strain through cheesecloth into glasses. Cover with 1/4-inch of paraffin.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Slice orange thinly.
Combine undiluted lemonade concentrate and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Garnish with orange slices. Makes 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Cook
pudding
and
milk
until it starts to boil.
Add yellow cake
mix
to pudding mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan
and sprinkle bag of butterscotch morsels over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not grease pan.

title: zucchini fudge cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually add the sugar and beat until lemon colored.
Add the vanilla and butter.
Combine and sift together the dry ingredients.
Pour half of the mixture over the egg mixture.
Add the buttermilk.
Add the remaining flour mixture.
Stir until combined.
Fold in the zucchini and nuts. Divide into two 9-inch round pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix grated softened cheese well.
Add all ingredients, except paprika and chili powder.
Form into 2 rolls on piece of wax paper.
Mix paprika and chili powder; roll balls in mixture to cover.
You may also use chopped nuts.
Balls may be frozen and refrozen.
Serve with crackers.

title: after church stew
directions: Place beef cubes in 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces.
Cover tightly.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 3 hours. Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.
Serves 5.

title: peppy lasagna
directions: In skillet, cook sausage, ground beef, onions, celery and carrots until meat is lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Simmer, uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook lasagna by package directions, drain.
Combine ricotta, Parmesan, eggs, parsley and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Place half the noodles in a greased baking dish.
Spread with half the cheese filling, add half the Mozzarella and half the meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.
Freezes well.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sherried crab soup
directions: Combine soups and cream in chafing dish or top of double boiler; heat just to simmering, stirring occasionally.
Add crab, sherry, parsley and seasonings; heat piping hot.
Serve at once in heated soup bowls.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: crunchy apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and add mayonnaise.
Makes 16 servings.

title: raspberry-rose geranium liqueur
directions: Combine berries, geranium leaves, vodka and wine in a large jar with a screw-top lid.
Place in a cool, dark place for 1 month to steep.
Crush berries with a wooden spoon and steep for another 4 days.
Strain the liquid, pressing as much juice from the berries as possible.
Filter liquid through a coffee filter.
Boil sugar and water together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Gradually stir into the liqueur, tasting for desired sweetness. Pour into a clean, decorative bottle and age 3 weeks before using.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
If not hot enough, sprinkle with cayenne pepper.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown beef, onions and chili powder. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and peppers; heat to boiling. Simmer 1 hour. Add beans last 15 minutes.

title: mystery pie
directions: Pour large box of Cool Whip in large bowl.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over this, chopped pecans, pineapple and juice of lemons. Pour in graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 1 cup.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter and slowly add honey. Cream well. Store in refrigerator. Serve on hot biscuits, rolls, pancakes or toast.

title: gerry's barbecue pork casserole
directions: Fry pork in 2 tablespoons margarine until brown.
Add onion, peppers, garlic, clove and margarine.
Cook until tender.
Add water, sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Bring all ingredients to boil.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let set for 10 minutes and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Weaken with water and sugar to taste.
Serves 50 people.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Mix in soup, water and mushrooms. Place browned pork chops on top of rice mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle with soup mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°; makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: whipped strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine egg yolks, half the sugar, salt, lemon juice and strawberries.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils.
Remove from heat and add the juice and gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Beat with hand beater.
Fold in whipped cream.
Beat egg whites with remaining sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: easy pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: best coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add all remaining ingredients, except butter.
Melt butter in pan and pour into batter.
Bake in slow oven at 250° to 300° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, then add water.
Stir until mixed very well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: calorie proctor
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Just as it begins to thicken, fold in two-thirds of the container of whipped topping.
Add cake pieces and fold together until well coated.
Pour into angel food pan (tube pan) and put in refrigerator to set.
Unmold on cake plate and ice with remaining whipped topping tinted a pale pink.
Decorate with fresh strawberries and mint leaves, if desired.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix salt, pepper and breadcrumbs. Dip leg quarters, one piece at a
time,
into
butter,
turning
to coat.
Roll into breadcrumb mixture until coated.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Serves 4.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, and condensed milk. Add chopped walnuts and marshmallows; mix well. Pour into buttered 9 inch pan. Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix like bread dough.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Shape into 4 or 5 rolls.
Bake for 4 hours and turn over and bake 4 more hours at 150° to 200° on middle rack.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into four squares.
Put the biscuits in an angel food cake pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients. Put the frosting on top of the biscuits.
Put in oven at 375° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: chinese beets
directions: Drain beets and reserve 1 1/2 cups of the liquid they were cooked in.
Place beets and ingredients that are listed plus reserved liquid in saucepan.
Mix well and cook 3 minutes over medium heat until thickened.
Let cool and then store in refrigerator.
May be served hot or cold.

title: fried squash
directions: Place the milk in a bowl.
Mix the salt, pepper and egg together in the bowl with the milk.
Beat together for 1 minute.

title: hot rise bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt; add hot water. Beat smooth.
Add oleo and 4 cups flour (add gradually).
Beat after each addition.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until double.
Form into rolls or loaves and let rise again.
Set oven to 350° and put in pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine first.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time), then flavoring.
Sift flour three times.
Add baking powder and salt on last sifting, then add flour and sour cream (rotating).
Mix all ingredients, approximately 15 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Some ovens only take 1 1/2 hours.
Mine takes two.
You will have to test with a toothpick.

title: grandmas date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates. Add soda. Set aside and cool completely. Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Stir in cooled dates. Pour into greased and floured 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup walnuts, chopped and 1/3 cup sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15 pan with graham cracker crumbs. Reserve 1 cup crumbs. Slice bananas crosswise and layer over crumb crust. Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch thick slices and place over bananas. Sprinkle ice cream with walnuts. Freeze until firm. Melt chocolate chips and butter; add powdered sugar and evaporated milk. Cook mixture until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Cool chocolate mixture, then pour over ice cream and freeze until firm. Spread Cool Whip over chocolate layer and top with reserved crumbs. Store in freezer. Remove 10 minute before serving. This will keep for several weeks. Serves 25.

title: maraschino cherry and cream cheese salad
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl and mash with a fork.
Drain juice off of cherries, chop and put in with cheese.
Drain pineapple and add to cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip a little before time to serve.

title: pickled beets
