directions: Cook beets in 1-inch boiling, salted water for 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel and quarter beets.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over beets.
Marinate several hours or overnight in refrigerator. Pour off part of liquid before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: italian tomato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush bread halves with dressing.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Sprinkle with basil.
Place bread on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bake in a 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put peaches in bottom of bowl.
Mix sugar, flour, vanilla and milk well.
Pour over peaches.
Cook in 350° oven for one hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together sugar, peanut butter and pecans.
Roll into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate and wax.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Lay on wax paper and let cool.

title: creamy white fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until soft ball stage.
Beat in white chocolate chips and marshmallow cream until melted.
Add nuts. Pour into greased pan and allow to cool.
Cut into squares and store in candy tin with waxed paper between layers of fudge.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: When cake is done, pour boiled mixture over cake.
Serve when cooled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well; pour into small greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Pour French dressing over beans in deep bowl and let set overnight.
Next day, drain off salad dressing and keep.
Layer beans in bottom of bowl along with onions, cheese and tomatoes. Pour dressing over layers and refrigerate.
Before serving, put shredded lettuce and crushed Fritos on top.
Great for cookouts!

title: apple crumble pie
directions: Slice apples
to make 5 cups.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together sugar, flour and lemon peel.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with topping and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk; beat this until it starts to thicken, then add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer with pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: fisolin(green beans)
directions: Clean beans and cut.
Cook until tender.
Mix 1/2 tablespoon flour in 1/2 to 1 cup sour cream.
Add this to the green beans. Season with salt.
Add the vinegar and some chopped dill.

title: pork chops or chicken and rice
directions: In oblong pan, put 2 cups rice, mushroom and celery soups, Lipton soup (dry), and 1/2 cup water; stir. Place chicken on top; push into mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain.
Remove stems from mushrooms; set caps aside.
(Reserve stems for another use.)
In a small skillet, cook sausage until no pink remains, stirring to break up any large pieces.
Drain off fat.
Stir together sausage and cheese.
Fill mushroom caps with about 1 teaspoon of the sausage-cheese mixture. Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Spoon salsa over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through. Sprinkle with green onion.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve chilled on lettuce.

title: carrot balls
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in carrots.
Roll into small balls and roll in nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased or Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple impromptu
directions: Prepare as for pie.
Put in well-greased 8-inch or 9-inch pie pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all vegetables, mixing well. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well, and pour over vegetables. Chill 24 hours. Drain before serving. 10-12 servings.

title: hot mushroom
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add flour.
Make into a ball. Wrap.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Take and boil your chicken for about 10 minutes or until tender.
Boil your bouillon cubes in water, then boil rice in chicken flavor water for about 5 minutes.
Add boiled chicken, butter and salt; cook for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Be sure to keep stirred, then pour in a bowl and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine lemon juice, garlic salt, cumin, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Slice poultry into thin bite size strips.
Add to juice minutes.
Toss lightly to coat and set aside.
Chop tomato and shred lettuce.
Set them aside in serving bowls.
Spray large skillet with nonstick spray.
Preheat skillet over high heat.
Add undrained poultry mixture, onion and green pepper to skillet.
Cook and stir for three minutes or until poultry is tender and no longer pink and liquid has evaporated.
Put in serving bowl.

title: melt-in-your-mouth potato casserole
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes in unsalted water until tender.
Allow to cool, then peel.
Grate on coarse side of a grater.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, make a layer of half the potatoes and half the onions, then salt and pepper.
Repeat with potatoes and onions.
Salt and pepper again heavily.
Sprinkle cheese over top and pour cream over all.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, cheese and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Ice when cooled.

title: green beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion in a large deep skillet 8 to 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender. Add water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix and coat.
Cook and cover over medium heat, 18 to 22 minutes, stirring occasionally, until beans are very tender.
Transfer to casserole or baking dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream.
Cook to 240° (soft ball). Remove from heat.
Add salt and butter.
Beat until mixture begins to grain (thicken).
Add vanilla and nuts and pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: iron skillet chocolate icing
directions: In a bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Place eggs in skillet.
Add milk, butter, syrup and vanilla.

Turn heat on medium and slowly cook, stirring constantly, until it begins to boil and sugar is dissolved. Punch holes in each cake layer. When you reach the top layer, beat the rest of the icing a little with mixer, then frost the top and sides.

title: pisellal prosciutto(peas with prosciutto)
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the onion and Prosciutto and saute until onion is translucent.
Add peas, salt, pepper and boiling water.
Cook, uncovered, until peas are tender.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Dredge the chicken in 1 cup of flour, sprinkled generously with salt and pepper. In a large skillet, heat fat until hot. Brown chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Reserve 1/4 cup of drippings and discard remainder. Return reserved drippings to a hot skillet. When hot again, sprinkle in 3 tablespoons of flour, stirring constantly. Brown the flour but do not burn. Slowly add the stock, stirring until well blended. Simmer over low heat for 4 or 5 minutes. Stir in salt and pepper and the mushroom slices with juice. Pour this over the chicken. Cover the baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon clover rolls
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add shortening and mix well.
Combine milk and lemon juice and add to mixture.
Place on floured surface; knead slightly.
Form dough into balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; put juice into a saucepan and fruit into a bowl. Heat fruit	juice
with cornstarch until it turns thick and clear. Remove
from
heat.
Add egg; mix and reheat until mixture bubbles.
Remove
and
cool.
Mix fruit and Cool Whip; add fruit juice
mixture.
Put
into	a mold and freeze.
If a decorative mold is
used, mandarin oranges and cherries can be arranged in a decorative pattern.

title: sara's pineapple cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, oleo and pecans together and pat into bottom of greased pan (12 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch).
Spread with drained pineapple.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, bell pepper, onion, celery and peas in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese. Spread over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon bits if desired.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place lettuce in bowl; layer each of the next 5 ingredients. Combine last 4 ingredients and cover lettuce mixture, sealing to the edges of the bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: washboard cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(Dough will be stiff.) Chill for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Butter your pan.
Put down a layer of potatoes, then a layer of cabbage.
Mix onion in.
Put rest of potatoes and cabbage in pan.
Pour chicken soup over it.
Place corned beef on top.
Place in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water, mixing until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thick and clear.
Quickly stir in egg yolks.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup lemon juice, salt and butter.
Cool for several hours.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil, at least 2-inches deep.
Brown on both sides.
Makes 15 to 20 small puffs.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs; beat until mixture is very stiff. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Freeze as directed in gallon freezer.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, salt to taste and drain.
Combine all ingredients and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lavosh (crackers)
directions: Preheat oven to 450° with lowest rack 6 inches from the bottom, the next rack 6 inches above it.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Add buttermilk, one tablespoon at a time, tossing dough with a fork to mix.
Once dough holds together, knead lightly on a floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
On floured waxed paper, carefully roll out each half into a 10-inch circle.
Invert onto a greased cookie sheet and remove paper.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with seeds.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, rotating cookie sheets between racks to assure even browning.
Cool on wire racks.
Just before serving, divide cheese between crackers and place in a warm oven until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: toffee
directions: Cook butter, margarine, sugar and water over medium heat, stirring often, for a very long time (until it reaches hard crack stage on candy thermometer, approx. 12 minutes). Use a heavy pan and stir with wooden spoon because it gets very hot!

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish or a 9-inch deep dish pie plate and set aside.
Combine flour and remaining sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: swiss and tuna spread
directions: Combine tuna, cheese and bell pepper in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well. Serve on crackers or bread.
Also, may be toasted.

title: flapjacks
directions: Rub dry ingredients into 2 heaping tablespoonfuls grease and add cold water for a smooth batter.
Fry in pan.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugars, butter, syrup, salt and vanilla
5 minutes and remove and stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and pour over corn. Bake at 250° about 1 hour.
Watch closely.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour with baking soda.
Mix margarine, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and egg until well blended.
Stir in half of flour mixture, then add nuts, apples and raisins.
Blend in apple juice, then remaining flour mixture.
Onto greased cookie sheets, drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sugars.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (makes 2 loaves).

title: duncan hines cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Break 2/3 bag of Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over cookies.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread half of mixture over cookies.
Mix pudding and spread over cream cheese.
Spread the other half of cream cheese over pudding.
Break the rest of cookies on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Add milk and sugar. Lightly beat egg yolks and add to melted chocolate mixture. Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Put into graham cracker pie shell and refrigerate.
Add fresh whipping cream on top.

title: red tomato wine
directions: Leave skins on peaches and oranges.
Put all ingredients together into large container with lukewarm water and let work for two weeks.
Stir every day.
Drain through cheesecloth and bottle in gallon jug and let stay for two more weeks before done.

title: mexican dip
directions: Take your sour cream and the package of taco seasoning.
Mix together in a small mixing bowl.
Transfer your mixture to a pie plate and smooth out like a cake batter.
Top your mixture with Mexican salsa and last, top with your shredded cheese.
Serve with Mexican tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: grace's salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and nuts. Fold in dry jello.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and layer sliced pineapple on top. Bake uncovered for 30 more minutes.

title: coconut-pecan balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt. (If dough is soft, cover and refrigerate until firm.) Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough around pecan halves to form 1-inch balls. Beat egg white and water with fork.
Dip balls into egg white mixture; roll in coconut.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 14 to 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: marinated vegetable dish
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar.
Heat until sugar melts.
Add salt and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables.
Let set overnight.
This does not have to cover vegetables, but if you use a whole head of cauliflower and broccoli you need to double or triple this.
Shake it once in a while to cover the vegetables.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Cut apples into small slices; cook with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, one at a time, with remaining ingredients.
Makes a thick cookie dough type batter.
Grease and lightly flour a tube pan.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into the pan; pour apples on top of batter, then add the other half of the batter.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: babe ruth balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut and chill.
Roll into bite-size balls, then dip into the chocolate and paraffin which were melted together.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Whisk oil and eggs in another until blended and smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until blended.
Add apples, nuts and raisins (mixture will be very stiff).
Spread evenly in prepared pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut up.
Save broth.

title: taco relish
directions: On a large round platter, spread both packages of cream cheese.
Pour on taco sauce; spread over cream cheese.
Add tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: south carolina chew bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter, mix in sugar well.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Then add flour mixture. Stir well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in the warm water. Set aside. In a separate bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, 3 Tbsp. butter, salt and scalded milk. Stir in the eggs and softened yeast. Gradually add the flour to form a stiff dough, beating after each addition. Cover and let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light and doubled in size, 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Roll out dough on a floured surface to a 20 by 15 inch rectangle. Spread with 1/2 cup softened butter. Mix 1 cup sugar with the cinnamon and sprinkle evenly over the buttered dough. Cut into two 15 by 10 inch rectangles. Roll up each, starting with the 15 inch side. Cut each rectangle into 12 to 14 slices. Place cut side down in a well greased muffin cup or in two 9 inch pans. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size; 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from pans immediately. Frost with butter frosting, if desired.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough on cookie sheet.
Press dough together to make one sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown. Let cool; mix dressing with cream cheese.
Stir in milk until spreadable.
Spread on dough.
Sprinkle with onion, broccoli and carrots.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let set for awhile before serving.

title: pork roast
directions: Put in pan fat side up.
Mix together spices and sprinkle over roast.
Place onion around roast.
Add water.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes last 45 mins. Uncover and brown last 15 mins

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine in mixer.
Beat at high speed for 15 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Put pineapple over this, then Cool Whip, then nuts, then cherries.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a baking dish and bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: jelly filled doughnut sticks
directions: Flatten each biscuit with fingertips into a 5 x 2-inch oval stick.
Spoon 1 teaspoon jam lengthwise down the center of each, almost to the ends.
Pinch edges together over filling.
Fry in deep fat.
Roll in sugar.
Serve warm.
Makes 10.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese with mixer.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth. Add lemon juice, flavoring and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put into graham cracker crust and chill well.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and vinegar.
Stir together well and add to drained pork and beans.
Stir and let simmer about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix soup, egg, mayonnaise and milk; mix with broccoli.
Put in casserole dish; put cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spiders and goldfish snack
directions: Mix together peanut butter chips and shortening in a large glass bowl. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted. Stir in pretzel sticks and crackers. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla with a mixer until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup fruit and mix for 30 seconds.
Pour into pie crust and chill in freezer for 2 hours. Top with remaining fruit and serve.

title: pear relish
directions: Chop pears, peppers and onions.
Mix together, then add salt. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Put up in sterilized jars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish; let it set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Good to serve with fruit salad.

title: spinach soup (danish)
directions: Add the spinach washed and chopped to the boiling stock. Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
Grind the whole thing in blender. Melt 1 1/2 ounces of butter in saucepan; remove the pan and stir flour in it.
With a wire whisk, beat the spinach into the saucepan; bring it to a boil.
Season the soup with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer for 5 minutes and stir occasionally.
Garnish each serving with a few slices of hard-boiled eggs.

title: oreo suprise
directions: Crumble Oreos.
Melt butter.
Mix oreos and butter.
Spread in botton of large dish, save 3/4 cup for top.
Mix milk and pudding together, add softened cream cheese until creamy (with mixer). Add Cool Whip little by little.
Pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: school back pack snack
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Store covered in airtight container until ready to pack for school.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cut up bacon very small; remove pits and slice olives.
Combine all the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, over lower heat, and cook until rice is finished.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: golden crown rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add crumbled yeast and allow to soften.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat in the flour to make a soft dough. Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: broiled sirloin and mushroom salad
directions: Slash edge of fat on meat to keep from curling; grill meat about 13 minutes on each side.
Cool meat and cut into 3/8-inch strips.
Arrange in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2. Place mushrooms on beef; top with pepper strips.
Mix remaining ingredients except salad greens and tomatoes; pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours, spooning marinade over vegetables occasionally.
Remove beef and vegetables with slotted spoon onto salad greens.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: coffee pot roast
directions: Place meat in bowl with lemon juice, salt, pepper, onion and garlic pieces (some of which have been inserted into meat). Marinate overnight.
Brown meat well in bacon fat.
Transfer to heavy skillet.
Pour coffee over meat in pan where meat was browned.
Add rest of seasonings and simmer until tender.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch.

title: fruit punch #1
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 6 cups cold water and cool.
Combine with pineapple juice and water and with orange juice and water.
Chill.
Put in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes or ice ring and serve cold.
Yield: 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cesare's christmas salad
directions: Cook the egg yolks, mustard and lemon juice on stove until thick; let cool.
(This is the dressing.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Chop peppers and onions. Mix together. Add the remaining ingredients. Put 2 to 3 tablespoons cooking oil in cast-iron frypan or other baking pan. Place in heated oven for few minutes. When cooking oil is hot*, pour corn bread batter in pan. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: yoriko's apple cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Good for breakfast or dessert.
Best served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: frozen cantaloupe
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Cook until the syrup gets syrupy.
Cool and chill.
Peel cantaloupe and cut into balls or bite size pieces.
Pour syrup over cantaloupe; freeze immediately.
Serve partly frozen for a real treat.

title: lunch sticks
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt; let cool.
Add beaten eggs, yolk, shortening, and nutmeg.
Add about 6 cups flour.
Add yeast water. Roll on board, kneading in rest of flour (about 10 min.).
Let rise till double, punch down.
Let rise then roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut in strips about 2x4.
Let rise 1 hour.
Deep fry at 375°.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off excess grease.
Add soup and salts. Simmer a couple of hours in the crock-pot.

title: coconut creme torte
directions: Bake a pie crust dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. In top of
double
boiler,
heat	milk, sugar and salt.
When mixture is hot,
thicken with cornstarch.
Add and stir until thick.	Add eggs, stirring into mixture.
Cool 4 to 5 minutes longer, stirring.
Add
vanilla, butter and coconut, stirring well.
Put into
cooled
pie
shell.
Chill.
Top with either whipped cream or Cool Whip and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Mix milk with mace.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add crab, roe, butter and cream; cook 15 minutes.
Thicken with cracker crumbs. Season with salt, pepper and onion.
Add sherry just before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine top 7 ingredients until fluffy.
Add pecans (whole or broken).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion and ham.
Drain most of water (about 3/4) and then add milk until potatoes, ham and onions are almost covered.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until done. Should be thick.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix celery, water chestnuts and chicken soup; put in a dish. Saute crackers and almonds in margarine; put on top of celery mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook a large Irish potato until it falls apart.
Drain and put through a ricer.
Add confectioners sugar until potato is the right consistency and knead.
(It goes to liquid when the first sugar is added.
Keep adding sugar.)
Use your favorite flavor, peppermint, wintergreen, orange or vanilla.
The candy can be patted into a flat piece on waxed paper and spread on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate.
When dry, turn over and spread on the other side. Refrigerate.
This candy can be molded and dipped in chocolate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotelle about 12 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Add all ingredients.
Stir and chill.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, flour and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or test with a straw; if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: popcorn bark
directions: Melt bark in the microwave as package directs.
Combine almond bark, corn and Fritos in large bag.
Pour melted bark on and mix quickly. Let cool and enjoy.

title: autumn meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into loaf and place in greased shallow baking dish or iron skillet.
Place in a 350° oven for 10 minutes while preparing sauce.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir in granola (slightly crushed) 1/2 cup at a time. Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Put M&M's on top of each cookie (as many as you like).
Bake until light brown (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool 2 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients. Take 1/3 of dough and roll out for crust. Makes 3 crusts.

title: snowball dessert
directions: Cream
margarine;
add	sugar
and
pineapple and nuts. Place a layer of vanilla wafers in bowl or dish, then layer of mixture and
layer	of
whipped
cream.
Repeat
and
top with coconut and decorate with cherries.

title: baked carrots
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes more.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well, then add 2 tablespoons flour, salt, and vanilla. Mix well. Add Karo and pecans that have been sprinkled with flour. Mix and then pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° in oven until cracks on top, about 35 minutes.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Saute onion in oil in a large skillet until tender, 3 minutes. Stir potato slices, sauce mix, water and milk.
Cut ham into cubes, add to the potato.
Bring to boiling, stirring frequently.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: super simple low-fat rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or until thickened.
Pour into dessert cups and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut butter (margarine) in pieces and mix all together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler, quick and easy
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Line square loaf pan (glass) with artichoke hearts.
Layer chicken over them.
Top with soup.
Bake 1
hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter; add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix by hand.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bar in a double boiler or microwave and spread on top.
Let cool; cut and pig out.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Cream cheese and add pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and salt mixed with lemon juice. Stir well.
Whip cream adding sugar and fold into jello mixture.

title: sourdough french bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, soften yeast in water.
Blend in 2 cups flour, sourdough starter, sugar, butter and salt.
Combine 1 cup flour and soda.
Stir into flour and yeast mixture.
Add enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead for 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth.
Let rise in greased bowl 1 1/2 hours, or until double.
Punch down and divide in half.
Cover and let set 10 minutes. Shape in 2 oblong loaves.
Place on greased baking sheet that has been sprinkled with cornmeal.
Let rise in warm place about one hour or until double.
Brush with water and make diagonal slashes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from sheet and cool.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla; cream again.
Sift and add dry ingredients together.
Mix with the shortening and egg mixture.
Add nuts and bake as drop cookies about 10 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually mix in baking soda, cream of tartar and flour. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gouda wrap
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove red wax from Gouda.
Unwrap crescent rolls and pinch together seams to form two rectangles. Wrap rolls around cheese in two sheets, until cheese is encrusted. Place in oven until crust is golden brown.
Remove from oven and serve with pepper jelly on top.
Serve hot on Triscuits crackers. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first four ingredients until crumbly.
Slowly add the liquids until dough forms.
Mix the water, egg and vinegar together.
Bake until browned at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Grease an 8x8-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl;
combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, and baking powder. Make an indentation in center.
Pour milk, oil, egg and milasses into indentation.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: june punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves sixty (1/2 cup size size).
Serve with cracked ice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low heat until ready to serve. Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: kielbasa and cabbage(microwave)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
quart
casserole dish (cabbage will cook down).
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave on
High 8 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp, stirring at four minute intervals.
Drain excess juice. Yield:
4 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; blend well. Beat at medium speed for 2 or 4 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in round cake pans.
Top with chocolate frosting after cooled.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles till done. Let noodles chill. Dice green pepper, add to chilled noodles add remaining ingredients. Mix pasta salad together and place in refrigerator to chill entire salad.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating constantly.
Stir flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately to mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla flavor. Grease and flour pan.
Cut wax paper and line bottom of pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from pan and dust well with powdered white sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
After jello starts to congeal, add other ingredients and put into mold.

title: pork loin roulade
directions: Place cutlets between two pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound with a mallet to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Place several red and green pepper strips crosswise on each portion of pork.
Roll up jellyroll style and secure with wooden toothpicks.
In a large heavy skillet, brown the pork rolls in hot oil.
Drain fat from pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to skillet.
Bring mixture to the boiling point.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until pork is tender.
Remove toothpicks to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter; smooth in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add the hot milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth, cream and chicken.
Heat well and add mushroom soup and diced egg yolks. Serve in patty shells or on thin, crisp toast.
Yields 40 servings.

title: fudgicles
directions: Cook according to package directions.
Cool and freeze in small paper cups.

title: orange and avocado salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, orange juice, paprika and salt.
Alternate slices of avocado and orange on lettuce leaves.
Drizzle with mayonnaise-orange dressing.

title: canadian meat pie (tourtiere)
directions: Cook above ingredients (except potatoes) together in skillet. Drain fat.	Add mashed potatoes to meat mixture.
Pour mixture in pie crust and bake at 350° till crust browns (approximately 30 to 45 minutes).

title: baked ham slice
directions: Trim rind or fat from ham; place in baking dish.
Mix mustard and sugar; spread on ham.
Pour enough milk to come almost to the top of the slice of ham.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderately slow oven until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with sliced pineapple, sauteed in butter.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, oleo and oil.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Shape into 2-inch balls; roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: popcorn surprises
directions: Measure popped corn into large bowl. In a small saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Cover tightly and bring to a rolling boil. Remove lid and add a thermometer. Cook to 270°. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour cooked syrup over the popped corn, stirring to coat corn. Cool completely, then run through a food chopper. Melt chocolate coating in top of a double boiler. Stir ground popcorn into chocolate, using as much popcorn as the chocolate will hold. Pack into chocolate-lined molds or roll out between waxed paper and cut into shapes with cookie cutters or a knife. Yield: about 50 pieces.

title: mel's south point soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add minced garlic, sliced ginger and chopped onion.
Cook until onion is wilted.
Add whole pork chops and cook until brown.
Pour in water and oyster sauce; simmer until pork chops are tender.
Chop cabbage and watercress into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Add stems of cabbage and cook 5 minutes at slow boil.
Add remainder of cabbage and watercress.
Simmer until soft.
Season with pepper.
Add tofu cut into cubes and turn off fire.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut and sugar, mixing well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill at least 12 hours.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers	and
put in large mixing bowl.	Add all other ingredients
and mix well.	Chill before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days. Do not freeze.

title: jelly meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs and soup mix.
Make into meatballs.
Put in a baking dish.
Mix chili sauce and grape jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: slaw
directions: Pour boiling liquid over cabbage and seal for 4 hours.
Stir and serve, or store in a sealed container in refrigerator.
This will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to a boil. Add peanuts and salt. Reduce heat to medium. Let cook until peanuts start popping (30 minutes); stir constantly. Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda. Pour on greased cookie pan.

title: fudgy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa and heat until mixture begins to boil, stirring constantly until smooth. Pour into small mixing bowl. Cool completely.
Alternately add powdered sugar and milk, beating to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Additional milk may be needed.

title: japanese noodle salad
directions: Slice ripe tomatoes 1/4-inch thick and place on a large plate. Dice scallions and some of green part and cover tomatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle oregano or basil over onions and add oil and vinegar, 3 oil to 1 vinegar, maybe several times.
Blend well and pour over mixture, then add grated Romano cheese over top.
Let set a little while, then serve.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream shortening and vanilla.
Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder and set aside.
Add eggs to cream mixture, one at a time, then add to mixture alternately 7 spoons of flour and 3/4 cup of buttermilk.
Add baking soda to remaining 1/4 cup of buttermilk and add to batter.
Add remainder of flour.
Drop by the spoonful onto a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Chop cabbage into small pieces.
Spread in bottom of casserole.
Brown onion and meat and stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Add tomato paste and water.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Take foil off.
Top with cheese and put back in oven only long enough to melt cheese.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture, slowly.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Roll on floured surface 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes with floured cutters.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet.
When cool, frost as desired.

title: pizza bubble bread(appetizer or snack)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle round pizza pan with cornmeal. Separate biscuits in tube.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and place in mixing bowl.
Add sauce and toss to coat.
Arrange pieces of dough into 8-inch circle on pan and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
To eat, break off pieces.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Boil raisins in 1/2 cup water to soften.)

title: vegetable squares
directions: Pat crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at temperature suggested on package.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Top with desired vegetables and press them lightly into crust.
Cut in squares when ready to serve.

title: beef with noodles
directions: Cook noodles until tender, according to package instructions. Drain well.
Place a clean towel over wire cooling racks.
Spread noodles evenly over towel and dry about 3 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers.
Remove seeds.
Put peppers in boiling, salted water for about 5 minutes.
Drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.)
Sprinkle inside or peppers generously with salt. Cook beef and onion until brown, seasoned with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pot roast
directions: Place potatoes in a slow cooker. Trim fat from roast; brown in hot oil on all sides in a skillet. Place meat in the slow cooker. Discard all but 1 Tbsp. drippings from skillet; saute onion until tender. Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and salt. Pour over meat and potatoes. Cover and cook on high for 4-5 hours or until meat is tender. Before serving, pour sauce into a skillet. Cook and stir over medium high heat until thickened; serve with potatoes and meat.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine raisins and water.
Cook in covered pan until water evaporates.
Cut up dates into hot mixture if desired.
Add oleo and shortening.
Stir until blended.
Add applesauce, vanilla and artificial sweetener.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture and blend until smooth.
Pour into pan and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Whipped cream or topping may be used with each serving.

title: celestial cake
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Pour boiling water on jello and dissolve.
Refrigerate jello until thick, but not set.
Add enough cold water to lemonade to make 2 cups.
Stir lemonade into jello.
Beat until foamy.
Fold Cool Whip into jello mixture.

title: cauliflower with bread crumbs
directions: Rinse cauliflower with cold water.
Place whole cauliflower in pot and fill with enough water to cover the cauliflower.
Add salt to water and cauliflower.
Cook cauliflower until tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Test tenderness by spearing with fork.
Drain off liquid.
Place cauliflower in bowl.
In small saucepan, melt butter on medium heat.
Add bread crumbs and saute until golden brown for a minute or two.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cauliflower.

title: tasty tuna spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with onion soup mix and tuna. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: sweet and sour little doggies
directions: Combine ingredients in pot. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with fruits. Grapes, strawberries and apples are our favorites!

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf or as a dip with corn chips.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Bring water, oil and salt to a boil in 4-quart saucepan.
Drop in shells.
Cook until tender.
(Do not overcook.) Stir gently. (Do not let them stick.)
Remove from heat; drain.
Let cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and garlic salt; spread on ham.
Roll up long way.
Chill, then slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Makes 36 to 40 bite size pieces.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Mix buttermilk, dill weed, sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Toss with cabbage, green pepper and carrot.
Garnish as desired with thinly sliced carrot flowers and ripe olives.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add creamed mixture, milk and coconut milk.
Stir in coconut.
Fold in eggs.
If you want cake to be white, just use egg whites.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat by hand until mixed.
Serve with apples, etc.

title: easy orange salad
directions: Mix together the cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add the jello and the mandarin oranges; refrigerate until ready to eat.
